"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"100 seo statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"ecommerce seo statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"local seo stats\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"search engine marketing statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"seo statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"video seo stats\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=22425\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:330:\"<p>Are you looking for up to date SEO statistics? We decided to compile a mega-list of 100 SEO statistics to help you update your SEO strategy for 2021.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/100-seo-statistics/\">100 SEO Statistics – Update Your Strategy for 2021</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41738:\"<p>Are you looking for up to date SEO statistics?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The world of search engine optimization (SEO) is complex and requires plenty of planning. <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Creating a website</a> or small business means you have to think carefully about your SEO strategy if you want to see your brand thrive. Understanding key SEO statistics will help you make smart and thoughtful marketing decisions in the future.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We decided to compile a mega-list of 100 SEO statistics with the goal of helping you get a better handle on your SEO so that you can get more email subscribers, sales, and traffic.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before we look at the stats, we&#8217;re going to answer a very important question: </p>\n\n\n\n<p>“What is SEO?” </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once we define the term, we’ll go over stats across various industries and platforms to get a better understanding of SEO and its impact on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get started!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We want to help you navigate our compiled SEO statistics as quickly and efficiently as possible. Here’s a table of contents you can use to find the section that appeals to you.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"is-style-default\"><li><a href=\"#what-is-seo\">What is SEO?</a></li><li><a href=\"#google-ranking-factor-statistics\">Google Ranking Factor Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#local-seo-statistics\">Local SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#ecommerce-and-small-business-seo-statistics\">eCommerce and Small Business SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#video-seo-statistics\">Video SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#voice-search-seo-statistics\">Voice Search SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#mobile-seo-statistics\">Mobile SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#search-engine-marketing-statistics\">Search Engine Marketing Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#off-page-seo-statistics\">Off-Page SEO Statistics</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-is-seo\">What Is SEO?&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"397\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo.png\" alt=\"What is seo? All in One SEO (AIOSEO)\" class=\"wp-image-22426\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo-300x169.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo-704x396.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo-600x337.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>First, let&#8217;s explain what search engine optimization is, also known as SEO. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Essentially, SEO is the process of optimizing your site to rank high in search engines like Google so you can get more traffic to your site. The goal is to eventually make it to the first page of Google for your chosen keywords.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, but what do keywords really mean, you may think?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-do-keyword-research-for-your-wordpress-blog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Keywords </a>are ideas and topics that define what your site&#8217;s content is about. In terms of SEO, they&#8217;re the words and phrases that searchers enter into search engines, also called &#8220;search queries.&#8221; You want the keywords on your page to be relevant to what people are searching for so they have a better chance of finding your content among the results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, making it to the elusive first page of Google means that more people will find your website, which opens the door to some pretty exciting marketing opportunities.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can strengthen your SEO ranking in many ways. Some businesses focus heavily on optimizing their website and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">fine-tuning their XML sitemap. </a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Others spend their time creating blog content and building a consistent traffic source from platforms like Facebook and YouTube, which correlates with improved search engine rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, high-quality content and link building are two of the most important ranking factors according to <a href=\"https://searchengineland.com/google-reveals-20-percent-queries-voice-queries-249917\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Search Engine Land</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The truth is, you need to consider all of this if you want to make your website accessible to a broad audience.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But that’s only the beginning.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO is complex and can take some time to fully grasp, especially if you’re <a href=\"https://www.blogtyrant.com/start-a-new-blog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">new to blogging</a> or running a small business. The journey to the front page of Google requires you to think carefully and use SEO statistics to make your content and marketing decisions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that we’ve defined SEO, let’s move on to the statistics.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"google-ranking-factor-statistics\">Google Ranking Factor Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can’t talk about SEO without bringing Google and ranking factors into the conversation. Google is the largest search engine in the world, and the most frequently visited website of all time. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, the number of Google searches increase every year.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - Google searches per year\" class=\"wp-image-22427\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year-300x208.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year-600x416.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://www.internetlivestats.com/google-search-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Internet Live Stats</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Because of Google’s popularity, its ranking system for websites based on search relevance and performance is the standard used by virtually all business owners.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, Google uses over<a href=\"https://backlinko.com/google-ranking-factors#pagelevel\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"> 200 factors</a> in their algorithm for ranking websites. These <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/seo-ranking-factors/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SEO ranking factors</a> include domain age, keywords, mobile-friendliness, number of internal links, and much more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out some more interesting Google ranking factor stats:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Out of all of the website traffic in the world, <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/216573/worldwide-market-share-of-search-engines/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">86%</a> goes through Google&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li><a href=\"https://videos.brightedge.com/research-report/BrightEdge_ChannelReport2019_FINAL.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">68%</a> of online experiences start with a search engine</li><li>Believe it or not, Google receives <a href=\"https://www.internetlivestats.com/google-search-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">3.5 billion</a> searches every single day</li><li>Research shows that <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/insiders/inbound-marketing-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">75%</a> of searchers don’t bother clicking past the results on the first page</li><li>The first 5 results for a given search account for <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/digital-marketing-statistics/#seostatistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">67%</a> of all clicks</li><li>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/blog/search-traffic-study/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">91%</a> of all websites never receive organic traffic from Google due to not having backlinks</li><li><a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/randfish/keepng-up-wth-seo-n-2017-beyond/11-Keyword_Length_of_Search_Queries1Word\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">54.31%</a> of search queries contain 3 or more words</li><li>The average person searches for something online <a href=\"https://ardorseo.com/blog/how-many-google-searches-per-day-2019/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">3-4 times</a> a day</li><li>Analysts predict that between <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/local-seo-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">16% and 20%</a> of all user searches are brand new keywords and phrases, which should get you excited about optimizing your content for new keywords</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>According to <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko</a> pages with shorter URLs are often given favor in search rankings, as well as sites with a lower bounce rate and faster loading times.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Check your loading times with <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/free-website-speed-test-tool-for-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">IsItWP’s FREE speed test</a> to see where you stand!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.searchenginejournal.com/google-algorithm-history/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Search Engine Journal</a> states that Google introduces thousands of changes to their search engine algorithm every year. With that said, if you want to win at SEO, you have to play by Google’s rules.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"local-seo-statistics\">Local SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>According to Google,<a href=\"https://www.socialmediatoday.com/news/12-local-seo-stats-every-business-owner-and-marketer-should-know-in-2019-i/549079/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"> 46%</a> of all Google searches are local. Local SEO is a little different from traditional SEO. Instead of targeting a global audience, it’s all about reaching people who live in a specific place.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Business owners that have brick and mortar locations may take to the internet to promote their brand. Similarly, companies that offer a service like plumbing or electrical work use local SEO to reach their target audience.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll want to target keywords that use words that focus on location. If you have a sushi restaurant, you would want to use a keyword like “Sushi restaurants near me.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s also important that you list your business on Google so you can appear in the rankings. Include information about your company that new customers may need to know, such as your business hours, phone number, and address.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Including this information makes it easier for people to contact your company, which leads to more sales and visibility.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s continue with some interesting local SEO statistics.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"294\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - mobile searches statistics \" class=\"wp-image-22430\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics-300x125.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics-704x294.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics-600x250.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Think with Google</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The terms “Where to buy” and “near me” increased<a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"> 200%</a> over the past 2 years and search queries for “(store) near me” have grown <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">250% </a>over the same 2 years. You might be surprised to learn that 28% of local business searches eventually turn into a sale.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Around one-third of all searches mention specific locations and 97% of people learn about local companies online more than anywhere else.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not to forget the growing number of mobile users. Did you know that <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/advertising-channels/search/how-advertisers-can-extend-their-relevance-with-search-download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">18%</a> of smartphone users made a same-day purchase after performing a local search? When asked, 54% of mobile users said they look up hours of local businesses, while <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/advertising-channels/search/how-advertisers-can-extend-their-relevance-with-search-download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">53% </a>looked up directions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a result, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">56%</a> of local businesses that don’t have a listing on Google are losing out on potential customers. This statement is reinforced by the fact that 72% of people that use local search end up visiting a store within 5 miles.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4 out of 5 consumers say they want more personalized offers that relate to their location, and about 70% of people said that businesses should put call and direction buttons in their ads.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>More importantly, allowing reviews for your local business can increase visibility and result in <a href=\"https://trustpulse.com/online-review-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">73%</a> more consumers trusting your brand.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On a final note, long-tail keywords, such as those used when coming up with local keywords, generate <a href=\"https://moz.com/beginners-guide-to-seo/keyword-research\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">70%</a> more traffic when compared to commonly used shorter words. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want more details on how to optimize your website, please check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide.</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"ecommerce-and-small-business-seo-statistics\">eCommerce and Small Business SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We can’t have a list of SEO stats and not mention the importance of SEO for eCommerce and small business owners. Brands around the globe work on improving their SEO, so they can reach a broad audience that’s interested in their product or service.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Business owners and marketing teams have a ton of cool tools they can to boost their SERP (Search Engine Result Pages) position.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The general theme is that you want to get as many businesses and consumers as possible to find out about your brand through social media, email, and by browsing Google.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s look at several small business and eCommerce SEO statistics you should keep in mind if you want to see your website make it to page 1 for your keywords.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"495\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - number of clicks on Google\" class=\"wp-image-22431\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics-300x210.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics-600x421.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/google-ctr-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An impressive <a href=\"https://retail.emarketer.com/article/more-product-searches-start-on-amazon/5b92c0e0ebd40005bc4dc7ae\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">35%</a> of all product searches begin with Google, and on average, <a href=\"https://www.brightedge.com/resources/research-reports/content-optimization\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">40%</a> of revenue comes from organic visitors. This is the free traffic that’s the most desirable for businesses, as well as for consumers it seems since&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.blogtyrant.com/new-blogging-statistics/#engagement-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">70-80% </a>tend to ignore paid content in favor of organic results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, leads from search engines have a 14.6% conversion rate, which beats out outbound marketing practices like cold calling by over 700%. Actually, <a href=\"https://www.brightedge.com/resources/research-reports/content-optimization\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">51%</a> of traffic from B2B and B2C sites comes from search.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that businesses spend close to <a href=\"https://moz.com/rand/seo-consultant-agency-pricing-structure-services/#32\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$5,000</a> every month on their SEO strategy, and will spend <a href=\"https://www.borrellassociates.com/industry-papers/papers/trends-in-digital-marketing-services-april-16-detail\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$79.27 billion</a> on SEO by the end of the year?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On-page content, such as your blog, can increase traffic by as much as <a href=\"https://www.marketingsherpa.com/content_by_legacy_id?legacy_id=32133\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">2000%</a>, which can directly impact your SEO ranking. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Similarly, businesses that blog get <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">524%</a> more pages indexed by Google, and <a href=\"https://neilpatel.com/blog/38-content-marketing-stats-that-every-marketer-needs-to-know/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">72%</a> of business owners and marketers claim that content creation is their number tool for improving SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Moving up 1 search engine results page (SERP) will boost your click-through rate by an average of <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/google-ctr-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">30.8%</a>, which is fantastic. To be able to do this, it could be a good idea to pay extra attention to <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko’s </a>research indicating that pages with at least one image, such as product pages, rank higher than businesses that only have descriptions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What is becoming more important for eCommerce businesses, is that the demand for same-day shipping is up <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/marketing-resources/omnichannel/meeting-shoppers-needs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">120% </a>compared to 2015, and that trend seems consistent in 2021. They better get their logistics on track so they can respond to this increased demand for same-day shipping.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, according to <a href=\"https://www.chatmeter.com/blog/growth-of-near-me-searches-shows-importance-of-local-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Chat Meter</a> responding to positive and negative feedback can help you improve your SEO ranking.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"video-seo-statistics\">Video SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing videos for SEO is now an extremely common practice. The surge of mobile devices and the ability to show YouTube results on Google make this a strategy you don’t want to miss out on in 2021.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can optimize your videos by including transcripts, creating a catchy title, and by using a thumbnail that matches the content, just to name a few things. Like other areas of SEO, all of these small tweaks can lead to significant results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s explore some video SEO stats so we can learn more about this brand-building technique.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"354\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - does video give you a positive return on investment \" class=\"wp-image-22432\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics-300x150.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics-704x354.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics-600x301.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To make you understand the incredible power of video content, we want to start by sharing that YouTube users watch <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/video-marketing-statistics-what-you-must-know/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">1 billion</a> hours of content every day. And according to <a href=\"https://www.marketingcharts.com/digital/video-110520\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Marketing Charts</a>, it’s estimated that by 2021, the average person will watch 100 minutes of video content every day.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine that!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>YouTube is the second-largest search engine in the world, with over <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/social-media-marketing-statistics/#YouTube-Social-Media-Marketing-Stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">1.9 billion</a> active monthly users, so this is a great source to tap into.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of <a href=\"https://www.renderforest.com/blog/video-marketing-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Render Forest’s</a> surveys revealed that only 7 out of 10 marketers optimize their videos for search-ability, which is a bad judgment since <a href=\"https://chipthompson.com/19-fascinating-statistics-case-visual-content-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">85%</a> of consumers in the United States only watch video content. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine the whole world!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Although, <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/state-of-video-marketing-new-data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">92%</a> of marketers say they plan on adding videos to their marketing strategy. They should really consider this based on the fact that <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/state-of-video-marketing-new-data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">88% </a>of marketers say that video delivers a positive return on investment.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, you’re 53% more likely to appear on the first page of Google if you add videos to your site, and you can also increase your organic SERP traffic by <a href=\"https://www.brightcove.com/en/blog/2015/08/create-compelling-video-experiences\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">157%</a>. That will surely lead to more conversions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The truth is that landing pages with videos get <a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/AdelieStudios/adelie-studios-top16videomarketingstatistics2016-56658453\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">80%</a> more conversions. Including a video on your landing page also increases your chances of appearing on page 1 of Google by 53%.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last but not least, we’ve already mentioned the importance of blog content. Blog posts with videos have a stunning <a href=\"https://www.convinceandconvert.com/content-marketing/year-of-video-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">53x</a> greater chance of making it to the first page of Google, and adding videos to your blog posts can help you get <a href=\"https://moz.com/blog/what-makes-a-link-worthy-post-part-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">3x</a> more inbound links.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"voice-search-seo-statistics\">Voice Search SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Voice search is quickly becoming one of the most popular ways consumers find out about brands around the world. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing your website for voice search means understanding what a consumer will likely say, instead of type. Strangely enough, these two things are often different, choosing the right keywords for voice optimization is crucial.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s now more convenient for people to simply talk into their phones or smart speakers instead of opening Google every time they have a question. Business owners and marketers realized that this trend was picking up early and got to work.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven’t started yet, don’t worry. It’s not too late to gear your site towards people using voice search.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But before you get started, here are some helpful voice search SEO statistics.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"261\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-22434\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1-300x111.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1-704x261.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1-600x222.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Think with Google</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The amazingly large number of 45 million people use voice assistants every single day, and Google Assistant usage has increased by <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/data/google-assistant-user-stats/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">400%</a> in the last year.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.nationalpublicmedia.com/smart-audio-report/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Edison Research and NPR</a> mean that 1 in 6 Americans owns a smart speaker, making voice a common way to browse the internet, and&nbsp; 22% with smart speakers use their devices to buy products. This goes hand in hand with the fact that 40% of millennials use voice search to buy things online.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What is more, <a href=\"https://www.pwc.com/us/en/services/consulting/library/consumer-intelligence-series/voice-assistants.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">61% </a>of people between the ages of 25 and 64 claim that they plan on using their smart speaker for searching more in the future, and by 2022, it’s predicted that <a href=\"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/voice-shopping-set-to-jump-to-40-billion-by-2022-rising-from-2-billion-today-300605596.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">55%</a> of households will have a smart speaker.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Almost <a href=\"https://www.seoclarity.net/next-generation-search-voice-17099/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">20% </a>of all voice searches are triggered by 1 word in a set of 25. The three most common trigger words include how, what, and best. Furthermore, the average word count of a voice search result page is 2,312 words.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And for all shopping lovers, did you know that Amazon and Google are responsible for <a href=\"https://www.strategyanalytics.com/strategy-analytics/news/strategy-analytics-press-releases/2018/01/02/loyalty-or-lock-in-most-smart-speaker-users-won%27t-budge-from-amazon-or-google\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">94%</a> of smart speakers used by consumers?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also be surprised to learn that <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">40.7%</a> of voice search responses come directly from featured snippets.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As mentioned earlier, turning your blog posts into video content can improve your organic traffic on that post by <a href=\"https://www.searchenginepeople.com/blog/8-blogging-stats-2017-strategy.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">157%</a>. According to <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/youtube-ranking-factors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko</a> comments on your YouTube videos play a significant role in your ranking on search engines.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Mobile SEO ties into many of the topics we’ve talked about today. Specifically, video and voice search have hit such a high level of success due to smartphone and tablet users.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"mobile-seo-statistics\">Mobile SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"325\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - digital around the world stats\" class=\"wp-image-22436\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics-300x138.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics-704x325.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics-600x276.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you’re optimizing your site or social media for SEO, you have to think carefully about the experience you’re providing for your mobile users. Sites that are not mobile-friendly can’t get ranked on Google, so mobile-readiness is a factor you need to consider.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t worry, we have your back. Here are plenty of mobile SEO statistics that will help you get started:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://wearesocial.com/blog/2020/04/digital-around-the-world-in-april-2020\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">5.16 billion</a> people have mobile devices, and over <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/277125/share-of-website-traffic-coming-from-mobile-devices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">51%</a> of internet traffic comes from smartphones and tablets</li><li>Google drives <a href=\"https://www.hubspot.com/marketing-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">96%</a> of mobile traffic, and <a href=\"https://www.go-globe.hk/local-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">87%</a> of all mobile users interact with a search engine daily&nbsp;</li><li>The first organic search result for any given keyword gets <a href=\"https://www.seoclarity.net/mobile-desktop-ctr-study-11302/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">27.7%</a> of all clicks, and <a href=\"https://www.brightedge.com/resources/research-reports/mobile-first-57-traffic-now-mobile\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">79%</a> of all keywords show different Google results depending on whether a user is on desktop or mobile</li><li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">16.8 billion</a> smart speaker devices were shipped out by Amazon, Google, Apple, and other brands</li><li>Mobile voice searches are <a href=\"https://searchenginewatch.com/sew/opinion/2296905/how-will-voice-search-change-seo-for-local-stores-global-enterprises\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">3x</a> more likely to be based on a specific location</li><li><a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/marketing-resources/omnichannel/meeting-shoppers-needs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">60% </a>of smartphone users have bought a product that they discovered by using a search engine</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>We obviously like our smartphones. According to <a href=\"https://www.emarketer.com/content/mobile-time-spent-2018\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Emarketer</a>, most people spend 3 hours and 35 minutes on their smartphones every day.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, <a href=\"https://searchengineland.com/8-major-google-ranking-signals-2017-278450\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Search Engine Land</a> states that websites that aren’t mobile-friendly don’t rank on Google. Based on the fact that 61% of mobile users will contact a website if they discover a business website with a mobile-friendly layout it’s extremely important to ensure your site is mobile friendly.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"search-engine-marketing-statistics\">Search Engine Marketing Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Search engine marketing, also known as SEM, is an extremely popular marketing tactic that you can use for more growth. Simply put, SEM is a strategy where brands try to increase their visibility on search engines by using paid advertisements.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The goal is to get more people to click on your website, which will help you get more conversions and grow your lead list. We think that SEM is best used when combined with other areas of SEO, and experts agree.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Data from SEM campaigns can help you learn more about your target audience, which in turn opens the door for more optimization opportunities.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"410\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - top 4 reasons people click on paid search ads\" class=\"wp-image-22438\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics-300x174.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics-600x348.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s show you some stats that confirm this statement. For starters, the average company sees a <a href=\"https://www.powertraffick.com/google-ads-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">200%</a> ROI with Google Ads, and <a href=\"https://databox.com/seo-vs-ppc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">86%</a> of experts use PPC (Pay Per Click) data to improve their SEO strategy. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a smart move because stats show that if a consumer clicks a PPC advertisement, they are <a href=\"https://www.wordlead.com/facts/ppc-statistics-adwords-trends/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">50% </a>more likely to buy a product when compared to organic traffic. They have higher shopping intent.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a matter of fact, one survey revealed that <a href=\"https://clutch.co/seo-firms/resources/search-engine-marketing-why-people-click-paid-search-ads\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">75%</a> of participants found paid search ads made finding what they were looking for easier, and 26% of people clicked on paid advertisements because they were familiar with the brand. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, 33% of respondents said they click on paid search ads because the promotional post answers their query.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not really surprising considering Google is the search giant, and in 2019, Google made over <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/266249/advertising-revenue-of-google/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$134 billion</a> in profits from prioritized search ads. However, the spending on text ads went down <a href=\"https://www.merkleinc.com/thought-leadership/digital-marketing-report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">14%</a>, but shopping on Google increased by 41% between 2018 and 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google is probably not crying crocodile tears since its advertising and search tools helped the company bring a staggering <a href=\"https://comparecamp.com/sem-statistics/#TOC3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$330 billion</a> to the U.S. market in 2018.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"off-page-seo-statistics\">Off-Page SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Off-page SEO is one of the most important aspects of growing your business. If other brands and websites aren’t linking to your company, and people aren’t sharing your posts on social media, you’re going to have a hard time ranking on Google.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Luckily, there are plenty of ways for you to improve your off-page SEO. We want to help you unravel the mystery once and for all by looking at some compelling off-page SEO stats.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"376\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - referring domain stats\" class=\"wp-image-22439\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics-300x160.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics-704x376.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics-600x320.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Ahrefs</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To start with, there’s a strong correlation between <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/social-media-and-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">social media popularity and SEO ranking</a> on Google. This is due to the fact that social media content is extremely shareable, so your site will get more traffic and visibility.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, articles shared on social media see a <a href=\"https://blog.hootsuite.com/social-media-seo-experiment/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">22%</a> performance increase compared to those not shared. Google even crawls social media for relevant information. It’s no surprise that <a href=\"https://databox.com/social-media-and-seo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">91%</a> of marketers spend time optimizing their profiles for maximum exposure.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Better yet, websites with blogs tend to get <a href=\"https://www.stateofinbound.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">97%</a> more backlinks, which is one of the most important factors for SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Generally, the top result on page one for a popular keyword has nearly <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">35,000 </a>backlinks. To build backlinks may seem like a walk in the park, but it’s not. In fact, <a href=\"https://www.smartinsights.com/digital-marketing-strategy/100-must-see-marketing-stats/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">65%</a> of marketers say that building backlinks is the most challenging aspect of SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And you soon realize the difficulty in building backlinks when&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/blog/search-traffic-study/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">66.31%</a> of pages don’t have a single backlink, as well as half of businesses use <a href=\"https://comparecamp.com/sem-statistics/#TOC3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">25%</a> of their budget to build links. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Other companies spend an average of $1000 per month on their link building strategy. It adds up!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ahrefs stats show that the number 1 position for a given keyword gets 5-14% more backlinks from new business websites, and better yet, infographics generate <a href=\"https://www.quicksprout.com/content-marketing-lessons-learned/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">37.5%</a> more backlinks than traditional content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On a final note, other tactics for <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/get-more-backlinks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">improving off-site SEO</a> include guest posting and giving testimonials to other businesses.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There you have it!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve now looked at over 100 SEO statistics that you can use to grow your business. You’re not going to see your business climb through the ranks overnight, but making it to page 1 of Google is entirely possible.&nbsp; </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">SEO </a>is a lot like life, the more you put in, the more you’ll get out of it. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to see your site beat the competitors and get tons of organic traffic, you have to put in the effort to optimize your brand for search optimization across all platforms.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thankfully, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a> makes the SEO process easy!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is the best WordPress SEO plugin, and it offers all the tools you&#8217;ll need to easily and efficiently optimize your site and improve search engine rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not using it yet? What are you waiting for?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Click here to get started with AIOSEO today!</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/100-seo-statistics/\">100 SEO Statistics – Update Your Strategy for 2021</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"https://aioseo.com/100-seo-statistics/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"How to Submit Your WordPress Site to Google News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:126:\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=submit-your-site-to-google-news\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 15 Dec 2020 13:00:39 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"google news publisher guidelines\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"google news seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"google news sitemap\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"google news submission\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"submit to google news\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"submit your site to google news\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=22262\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:385:\"<p>Do you want to know how to submit your WordPress site to Google News? In this post, we’ll explain how to do this fast and easy. We\'ll also cover how to add your site to Google Publisher Center.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/\">How to Submit Your WordPress Site to Google News</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42517:\"<p>Do you want to know how to submit your WordPress site to Google News? Submitting your site to Google News is a great opportunity to get ahead of your competition and start the new year ready to crush it in your niche.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Google News, you can break news quickly and efficiently. It’s a smart way to improve your site’s authority and increase search engine rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s exactly what we’re here to help you with, so in this post, we’ll explain how to submit your WordPress site to Google News.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Since this is a comprehensive post, we&#8217;ve created a table of content so that you can easily navigate and jump to the sections you want:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#what-is-google-news\">What Is Google News</a></li><li><a href=\"#why-should-you-submit-your-website-to-google-news\">Why Should You Submit Your Website to Google News?</a></li><li><a href=\"#follow-google-news-publisher-guidelines-is-a-must\">Follow Google News Publisher Guidelines Is a Must</a></li><li><a href=\"#add-your-site-to-google-publisher-center\">Add Your Site to Google Publisher Center</a></li><li><a href=\"#submit-your-wordpress-site-to-google-news-fast\">Submit Your WordPress Site to Google News Fast</a></li><li><a href=\"#optimizing-for-google-news\">Optimizing for Google News</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-is-google-news\">What Is Google News?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://blog.google/products/news/look-how-news-google-works/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google News</a> was created in 2002, and since then, in typical Google fashion, it has become one of the largest news aggregators online, serving content from over 75,000 sources in 62 languages across the world.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google News hand selects a flow of recent news articles and stories from the last 30 days. The news is sourced from all over the world. The prime objective of Google News is to give recent updates to its readers, and it consists of all types of news, including Global and local reports.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, Google News articles appear at the top of search results, as well as in their own dedicated news tab in Google, which makes these publications far more likely to get clicked on.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s what Google News looks like:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"626\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-feed.png\" alt=\"Google News feed\" class=\"wp-image-22266\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-feed.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-feed-300x257.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-feed-600x515.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The news content is organized into categories, depending on your location and language settings. As a reader, you can customize the feed to cover stories you are interested in.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"why-should-you-submit-your-website-to-google-news\">Why Should You Submit Your Website to Google News?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You may wonder why you should submit your website to Google News? The simple answer is that Google News is one of the most trusted windows in the world that provides users access to trending news topics from various corners of the world.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To submit to Google News has several benefits, and here are a few of them:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Brand awareness – if your site gets featured on Google News, you can say that Google is endorsing your content, which will naturally boost visibility and increase brand awareness.</li><li>More organic and targeted traffic – best of all is that you’ll get lots of organic traffic (free traffic). Google News can also expand your reach, so your content will be seen by your target demographic.</li><li>More backlinks – you’ll have a much higher chance of getting your link picked up by a major news outlet. Getting featured on Google News also improves your domain authority, which can increase referral traffic to your site.</li><li>Higher Google rankings – your Google News publication will also be added to the main search results, which can improve rankings. In addition, your site will also be indexed much faster.</li><li>Authority status – when your site gets featured on Google News, it automatically suggests that you carry quality information. It will add credibility to your site and therefore attract a larger audience.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>These are just a few of the benefits, so you probably understand by now that it&#8217;s really worth it submitting your site to Google News.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"follow-google-news-publisher-guidelines-is-a-must\">Follow Google News Publisher Guidelines Is a Must</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>But before you do anything, we need to mention that it’s crucial to follow the <a href=\"https://support.google.com/news/publisher-center/?hl=en-GB#topic=9603441\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google News content policies</a>. If not, your site will be rejected before you even started on your first publication.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"850\" height=\"448\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-content-policies.png\" alt=\"Google News content policies\" class=\"wp-image-22267\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-content-policies.png 850w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-content-policies-300x158.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-content-policies-768x405.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-content-policies-600x316.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Google works as such it sends out crawlers that scan the web for updates and then indexes those updates. Like Google itself, Google News also has crawlers, but they mostly crawl and index sites and content that comply with its content policies.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, if you don’t follow the rules and make sure all content conforms to the guidelines set by Google News, your site will be rejected.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, advertisements must be limited, and copyrighted content is expressly prohibited. Vulgar and sponsored content is also restricted.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We recommend that you read the content policies carefully, so you won&#8217;t lose out on the benefits of a Google News feature.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"add-your-site-to-google-publisher-center\">Add Your Site to Google Publisher Center</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The first thing you need to do is add your site to <a href=\"https://publishercenter.google.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google Publisher Center</a> and have it approved. If you’ve already done this, you can skip ahead to our tutorial on <a href=\"#submit-your-wordpress-site-to-google-news-fast\">how to submit your WordPress site to Google News</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add your site to Google Publisher Center, you need to have access to a Google account. You should already have an account connected with your site if you’re using Google Search Console, Analytics, or Tag Manager.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To begin with, sign in with your Google account or create a new one using any email address.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Submit Your General Information</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, visit the Publisher Center and click on <strong>Add publication</strong> in the left-hand menu.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"436\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-publication.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add publication\" class=\"wp-image-22268\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-publication.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-publication-300x179.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-publication-600x358.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Enter the name of your publication in the pop-up window and click on <strong>Save</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"385\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-new-publication.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add a new publication\" class=\"wp-image-22271\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-new-publication.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-new-publication-300x158.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-new-publication-600x316.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A publication lets you manage how your content is viewed by users in Google News, and the name should be unique to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After naming your publication, you’ll be redirected to a new window, where you need to fill in your site’s <strong>Basic information</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"564\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-general-information.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-22272\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-general-information.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-general-information-300x232.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-general-information-600x464.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll now see the name of your site or publication in the <strong>Publication name </strong>field. All fields are required to fill in to move on to the next step. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you need to modify the publication name, you can do so at a later stage. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The next step is to provide a <strong>Description</strong> of your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"564\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-description.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add description of your site\" class=\"wp-image-22269\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-description.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-description-300x232.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-description-600x464.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure your description is at least 140 characters. It needs to be an accurate description of your site’s content so that users can use this information to search for your publication in Google News.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, you need to set a <strong>Category</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"564\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-category.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add category\" class=\"wp-image-22274\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-category.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-category-300x232.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-category-600x464.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the drop-down menu, you need to categorize your site by the type of content it offers. This will help readers find your content easier.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve chosen a matching category, you need to select the <strong>Primary language</strong> of your site. This is required to later be able to add a location.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"564\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-primary-language.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add primary language\" class=\"wp-image-22275\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-primary-language.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-primary-language-300x232.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-primary-language-600x464.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can decide whether you&#8217;d like to turn on <strong>automatic translation</strong> to allow readers to view your content in their preferred language. Automatic translation is enabled by default, so you can just uncheck the blue box if you don’t want to use it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That being the case, we recommend that you only use one language since the Google News system can have problems crawling content that’s using multiple languages.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you’ll need to enter the <strong>Website property URL</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"467\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-website-property.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add website property URL\" class=\"wp-image-22276\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-website-property.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-website-property-300x192.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-website-property-600x384.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s important that you have Google Search Console ownership to get your URL verified. For more details, please visit WPBeginner’s post on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-add-your-wordpress-site-to-google-webmaster-tools/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to add your WordPress site to Google Search Console.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> You can only create one publication per website property.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After entering the correct website address or URL, you need to select the<strong> Location</strong> where your headquarters is located.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"467\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-location.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add location\" class=\"wp-image-22277\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-location.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-location-300x192.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-location-600x384.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If this is your first time setting up your site for Publisher Center, this won’t be available until your URL is verified in Google Search Console.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the event that you need to update your location, you can contact Google and ask them to update it through their <a href=\"https://support.google.com/news/publisher-center/contact/news_default\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">contact form.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once your URL is verified and you’ve added your location, you need to add <strong>Contacts</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"467\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-contacts.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add contacts\" class=\"wp-image-22278\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-contacts.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-contacts-300x192.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-add-contacts-600x384.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on <strong>+ New contact</strong> and list the email addresses of your contacts and what topic they should be contacted for. This is if Google News needs to get in touch with someone in your organization about your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you need to decide the <strong>Distribution</strong> of your publication.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"538\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-distribution.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center decide distribution of your publication \" class=\"wp-image-22279\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-distribution.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-distribution-300x221.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-distribution-600x442.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, your publication is available to readers worldwide, but you can use the drop-down menu to specify where you&#8217;d like your content to be distributed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if there are specific countries or regions where you would like your content to be restricted on Google News, this is where you can configure that.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also choose if you want your content to appear on all Google products (e.g., Chromecast, Google Play, etc.), or just a few.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Any changes to your international distribution settings will be effective immediately.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, you’re almost finished adding your basic information. The last step is to enable <strong>Tracking </strong>of your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"538\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-tracking.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add Google Analytics tracking ID\" class=\"wp-image-22280\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-tracking.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-tracking-300x221.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-tracking-600x442.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the <strong>Google Analytics tracking ID for app</strong> window, you can add Google Analytics tracking information for both your app and for <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/google-amp-future-of-mobile-seo/\">AMP (Accelerated Mobile Pages)</a>. You also have the option to add third-party tracking pixels.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;re finished adding all your general information, click on the <strong>Next</strong> button at the bottom right of the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Submit Your Content Information</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, we’ll move on to describing your site’s content with first adding <strong>Sections</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"449\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-new-section.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add a new section\" class=\"wp-image-22281\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-new-section.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-new-section-300x185.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-new-section-600x369.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the<strong> + New section </strong>and fill in all relevant fields depending on your needs. A section organizes content in your publication under the same topic in the Google News app, such as &#8220;Latest,&#8221; &#8220;Business,&#8221; &#8220;Sports,&#8221; or &#8220;Fashion.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In <strong>Feed options</strong>, you can create sections using <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/rss-content/\">RSS feeds</a>, web locations, or YouTube channels/playlists as content source.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"632\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-feed-options.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add feed options\" class=\"wp-image-22282\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-feed-options.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-feed-options-300x260.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-feed-options-600x519.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Based on the sections you provide, Google will create a top navigation for your site, so it&#8217;s important to choose the top 3–5 section titles that you’d like users to access content from.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We recommend choosing<strong> &#8220;Generating articles directly from feed and crawl&#8221; </strong>since this provides the most coverage.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After you’ve chosen your feed options, we’ll move on to setting up<strong> Content labels </strong>for your publication.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"474\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-content-labels.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add content labels\" class=\"wp-image-22283\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-content-labels.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-content-labels-300x195.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-content-labels-600x390.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can add labels for news sections that contain opinion, satire, user-generated, press release, or blog content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Importantly, all content labels need to accurately represent what they’re about, so only choose from label options that fits your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The last step in submitting your content information is to <strong>Verify URL ownership.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"474\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-verify-url-ownership.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center verify URL ownership\" class=\"wp-image-22284\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-verify-url-ownership.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-verify-url-ownership-300x195.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-verify-url-ownership-600x390.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on <strong>+ New content source</strong> to verify URL ownership. This step is important since all content associated with your publication must be from a verified domain.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information, please check out Google&#8217;s documentation on <a href=\"https://support.google.com/news/publisher-center/answer/9548309\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">verifying your content.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Submit Your Images (Logos)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s move on to images and submitting your<strong> Square </strong>and<strong> Wide logos.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"402\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-square-logo.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add square logo\" class=\"wp-image-22285\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-square-logo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-square-logo-300x165.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-square-logo-600x330.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you need to add the logo that will be shown for your site. You can use either a square, a wide logo, or both.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, adding a logo is a good way of branding your business, as well as customizing the user experience and representing your publication in Google News.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For the <strong>Square logo</strong>, it’s recommended to use a 1000&#215;1000 pixel logo in PNG, even that a JPEG down to 512&#215;512 pixels is also accepted.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last but not least, Google News recommends that you also add a <strong>Wide (rectangle) logo.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"609\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-wide-logo.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add wide logo\" class=\"wp-image-22286\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-wide-logo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-wide-logo-300x250.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-wide-logo-600x501.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The rectangle logo is recommended to be 400 pixels wide (but no less than 200 pixels) in PNG format.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Furthermore, it needs to include the publication&#8217;s full name in readable text with a max width-to-height ratio that doesn&#8217;t exceed 10:1. If available, you should also provide different versions for light and dark modes.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Submit Your Ads Information</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you need to submit your ads information in<strong> Earnings.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"497\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-ads-earnings.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add your ads earnings\" class=\"wp-image-22288\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-ads-earnings.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-ads-earnings-300x204.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-ads-earnings-600x408.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the drop-down menu, you can connect a Google AdSense account to be able to receive payment. If you haven’t heard of Google AdSense before, please check out WPBeginner’s post on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-add-google-adsense-to-your-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to add Google AdSense in WordPress.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>In short, the options appearing in the drop-down menu will be the Google AdSense account/s associated with the Google account you signed in with.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, we need to move on to<strong> Google-managed ads.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"497\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-google-managed-ads.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center Google-managed ads\" class=\"wp-image-22289\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-google-managed-ads.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-google-managed-ads-300x204.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-google-managed-ads-600x408.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can control how much of your ad inventory you want Google to manage. As a matter of fact, Google can sell ads to show in your Google News publication, which you’ll receive payment from. This is a good way of monetizing your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Submit Your Advanced Information</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the advanced tab, there’s an option to add <strong>Access groups.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"398\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-access-groups1.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center add access groups\" class=\"wp-image-22290\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-access-groups1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-access-groups1-300x164.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-access-groups1-600x327.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on <strong>+ Add user</strong> to set up access groups. This allows you to restrict sections of your publication to specific people, such as authorized testers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The email addresses you add must be associated with a Google account.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After you’ve created an access group, you can go back to the Content tab (in the main/top navigation menu) and assign it to a section.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Review and Publish</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’re done filling out all of the tabs, you can review any missing items in <strong>Google News app publishing status</strong>, as well as test your application.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"466\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-review-and-publish.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center review and publish\" class=\"wp-image-22291\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-review-and-publish.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-review-and-publish-300x192.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-review-and-publish-600x383.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the blue <strong>Review</strong> link to the right to check what information is missing and what you need to complement with.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you can go ahead and test your publication with clicking on <strong>Follow publication</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"227\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-testing-your-application.png\" alt=\"Google Publisher Center testing your publication\" class=\"wp-image-22347\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-testing-your-application.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-testing-your-application-300x93.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/publisher-center-testing-your-application-600x187.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The last step before clicking on the <strong>Publish</strong> button and submitting your publication for review is to sign off on the terms of service.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re lucky, the review process will be ready within 2 weeks, although it generally takes longer.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"submit-your-wordpress-site-to-google-news-fast\">Submit Your WordPress Site to Google News Fast</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"378\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-sitemap.png\" alt=\"How to submit your WordPress site to Google News fast\" class=\"wp-image-22339\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-sitemap.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-sitemap-300x161.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-sitemap-704x378.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-news-sitemap-600x321.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you’ve added your site to Google Publisher Center, we’ll show you how to submit your WordPress site to Google News.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the past, you had to manually submit your site to Google News for it to be considered. That’s not the case anymore, and publishers are automatically considered for top stories or the news tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With this in mind, it’s still recommended that you create a Google News Sitemap, which makes the process of submitting your site to Google News very fast and easy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You want to get ahead of your competition, right?!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you answered YES on that question, we’ll show you how to create a Google News Sitemap in a second. But first, let’s explain what it is, so you understand why you should create one.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>What Is a Google News Sitemap?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A Google News Sitemap is a special sitemap that only includes news publications. It enables Google to quickly find your articles and display them in the news search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Google News Sitemaps are not the same as standard Google Search Sitemaps, and they should only include news articles. For this reason, you need to create a new sitemap in order to submit your site to Google News.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whereas you don’t have to have a sitemap for Google News (and Google in general), your chances of getting your content crawled faster and better are much higher when you provide one.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s move on to showing you how to create a Google News Sitemap using one of the most popular WordPress plugins, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO).</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Create a Google News Sitemap</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO, you can create a Google News Sitemap fast and easy as 1-2-3. In fact, if you have a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Pro</a> <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">or</a> <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Elite</a> plan there&#8217;s only minor configuration needed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, go to <strong>Sitemaps</strong> in the <strong>All in One SEO</strong> menu and then click on the <strong>News Sitemap</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"342\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-menu.png\" alt=\"How to submit your WordPress site to Google News - create a Google News Sitemap using AIOSEO \" class=\"wp-image-22293\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-menu.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-menu-300x141.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-menu-600x281.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will take you to the&nbsp;<strong>News Sitemap</strong>&nbsp;window. Next, make sure the <strong>Enable Sitemap</strong>&nbsp;button is switched to on.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"712\" height=\"362\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/enable-news-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-menu.png\" alt=\"How to submit your WordPress site to Google News - enable news sitemap in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-22294\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/enable-news-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-menu.png 712w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/enable-news-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-menu-300x153.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/enable-news-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-menu-600x305.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 712px) 100vw, 712px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s off, you’ll see a grey button instead of a blue, and you need to turn it on.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once the Enable Sitemap button is switched on, you need to decide what content you want to include in the News Sitemap. To do this, you need to scroll down to <strong>News Sitemap Settings.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"708\" height=\"276\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-publication-name-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"How to submit your WordPress site to Google News - add a publication name in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-22295\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-publication-name-all-in-one-seo.png 708w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-publication-name-all-in-one-seo-300x117.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-publication-name-all-in-one-seo-600x234.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 708px) 100vw, 708px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can see the settings for <strong>Publication Name</strong> and <strong>Post Types</strong>. Enter the name of your publication in the <strong>Publication Name</strong> field. If you don’t enter a name, AIOSEO will automatically use your site’s title<strong>.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the <strong>Post Types</strong> setting, you select which content you want to include in your sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"708\" height=\"276\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-post-types-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"How to submit your WordPress site to Google News - add post types in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-22299\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-post-types-all-in-one-seo.png 708w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-post-types-all-in-one-seo-300x117.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-post-types-all-in-one-seo-600x234.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 708px) 100vw, 708px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can view a list of all your posts. Simply click on the ones you want to include.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The Google News Sitemap will only contain content published in the last 48 hours. If you haven’t published any content within the last 48 hours, you’ll see a 404 Page Not Found error, which is normal.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"708\" height=\"276\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-include-all-post-types-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"How to submit your WordPress site to Google News - include all post types in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-22298\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-include-all-post-types-all-in-one-seo.png 708w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-include-all-post-types-all-in-one-seo-300x117.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-include-all-post-types-all-in-one-seo-600x234.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 708px) 100vw, 708px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, if you want to include all posts, you can check the box <strong>Include All Post Types</strong>&nbsp;so it turns blue.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Needless to say, you should only include news content in your Google News Sitemap. For example, pages are unlikely to become news articles, so you shouldn’t include them in your sitemap. The same goes for products if you’re running an eCommerce store on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In <strong>Advanced Settings</strong>, you can choose what posts to exclude.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"708\" height=\"216\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-advanced-settings-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"How to submit your WordPress site to Google News - exclude posts or pages i AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-22300\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-advanced-settings-all-in-one-seo.png 708w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-advanced-settings-all-in-one-seo-300x92.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-advanced-settings-all-in-one-seo-704x216.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/news-sitemap-advanced-settings-all-in-one-seo-600x183.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 708px) 100vw, 708px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Just enter the name of the post you want to exclude and AIOSEO will search for it. Once your post shows up, you click on it, and it will be removed from your sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you’ve excluded the posts you don’t want to include in your sitemap, click on <strong>Save Changes</strong>. Now, you can go ahead and view your sitemap by clicking the <strong>Open Sitemap</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"117\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/open-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-1.png\" alt=\"How to submit your WordPress site to Google News - open Google News Sitemap in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-22739\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/open-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/open-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-1-300x48.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/open-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-1-600x96.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve now created a Google News Sitemap that will be submitted to Google News without you needing to lift another finger.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"optimizing-for-google-news\">Optimizing for Google News</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Last but not less important, have you heard of Google News SEO? Yes, that’s also a thing to consider when you’re competing for Google News features and spikes in organic traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve listed the most important factors to consider if you want Google News to vote for your publication. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>We recommend that you:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Add your site to Google Publisher Center (this we’ve already shown you how to do)</li><li>Conduct <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-do-keyword-research-for-your-wordpress-blog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">keyword research</a> to find news search terms that people are likely to use</li><li>Write a clear and concise headline, and use subheads and text formatting for emphasis</li><li>Always publish original and timely news content</li><li>Be transparent on your sources</li><li>Include photos and videos to improve user experience</li><li>Add meaningful links to direct your audiences to relevant additional content</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Needless to say, your website should be a news site. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>To conclude, these Google News SEO factors may seem obvious but are important to make sure that your Google News efforts will be successful and that Google votes for your publication. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want more tips on how to optimize your site, please visit our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide. </a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you understand how to submit your WordPress site to Google News. Take advantage of the opportunity to be featured in Google News so that you can get ahead of your competition and get that well-deserved increase in organic traffic and visibility.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Make Google News features a reality with the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">AIOSEO Pro or Elite plan</a>!</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/\">How to Submit Your WordPress Site to Google News</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"How to Add Nofollow Links in WordPress (In Just 2 Clicks)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:140:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-nofollow-links-in-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-add-nofollow-links-in-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-nofollow-links-in-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 08 Dec 2020 13:00:05 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"add nofollow links AIOSEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"add nofollow links in wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"All in One SEO Pack\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"follow vs nofollow\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"how to add nofollow links\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"nofollow links\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=21502\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:415:\"<p>Do you want to know how to add nofollow links in WordPress in just 2 clicks? In this post, you’ll learn how to add nofollow links in WordPress. We’ll also cover what nofollow links are and why they matter.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-nofollow-links-in-wordpress/\">How to Add Nofollow Links in WordPress (In Just 2 Clicks)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11686:\"<p>Do you want to know how to add nofollow links in WordPress in just 2 clicks?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Perhaps you’ve heard of nofollow links, but you’re not sure what they are or why you should use them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ll help you figure this out!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, you’ll learn how to add nofollow links in WordPress in just 2 clicks. We’ll also cover what nofollow links are and why they matter.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s a quick overview of what we’ll cover in this post. Simply click on these quick links to jump straight to different sections.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul id=\"what-are-no-follow-links\"><li><a href=\"#what-are-nofollow-links\">What Are Nofollow Links?</a></li><li><a href=\"#add-nofollow-links-in-wordpress-using-aioseo\">How to Add Nofollow Links in WordPress the Easy Way</a></li><li><a href=\"#why-are-nofollow-links-important\">Why Are Nofollow Links Important?</a></li><li><a href=\"#how-to-check-if-a-link-is-nofollow\">How to Check if a Link is Nofollow?</a></li><li><a href=\"#when-should-you-add-nofollow-links\">When Should You Add Nofollow Links?</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s start by explaining what nofollow links are.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-are-nofollow-links\">What Are Nofollow Links?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Nofollow links are hyperlinks with a rel=“nofollow” link attribute. You can turn any link into a nofollow link by adding this link attribute. The &#8220;nofollow&#8221; attribute tells Google and other search engine bots not to follow the link.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s what the HTML code of a nofollow link looks like:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;a href=\"https://example.com\" rel=\"nofollow\"&gt;Click Here&lt;/a&gt;</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>Why tell bots not to follow a link?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Because a link to a website is considered a vote of confidence. By linking to a website, you&#8217;re telling Google that you vouch for the website and its contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google created the nofollow attribute to limit spam and the number of low-quality content in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the nofollow attribute helps you to include links on your website without voting for them to be higher in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s the easiest way to add nofollow links in WordPress, without having to code:</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"add-nofollow-links-in-wordpress-using-aioseo\">How to Add Nofollow Links in WordPress the Easy Way</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to add nofollow links in WordPress is by using the AIOSEO plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">best SEO plugin for WordPress</a>. It has all the tools you need to optimize your site to rank high and get maximum search traffic, without being an SEO expert.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO also lets you add the nofollow attribute without needing to edit any HTML code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first thing you need to do is install and activate the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">AIOSEO plugin</a>. If you haven&#8217;t installed a plugin before, please visit WPBeginner’s step by step guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, head over to your blog post editing page. Add the anchor text for your link, select the anchor text, and click on the <strong>link </strong>icon.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"240\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/adding-nofollow-links-in-wordpress.png\" alt=\"Add nofollow links in WordPress \" class=\"wp-image-21910\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/adding-nofollow-links-in-wordpress.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/adding-nofollow-links-in-wordpress-300x102.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/adding-nofollow-links-in-wordpress-704x240.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/adding-nofollow-links-in-wordpress-600x204.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, you simply insert your external link in the window and click on <strong>Add “nofollow” to link</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"510\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-add-nofollow-link.png\" alt=\"Add nofollow links in WordPress - add &quot;nofollow&quot; to link\" class=\"wp-image-21911\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-add-nofollow-link.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-add-nofollow-link-300x210.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-add-nofollow-link-600x419.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once the nofollow attribute is added to your external link, you’ll see the <strong>Add “nofollow” to link</strong> button turn blue.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"510\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-add-nofollow-link-on.png\" alt=\"Add nofollow links in WordPress - add &quot;nofollow&quot; to link\" class=\"wp-image-21913\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-add-nofollow-link-on.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-add-nofollow-link-on-300x210.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-add-nofollow-link-on-600x419.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, press <strong>Enter</strong> on your keyboard and the link is added.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As simple as that!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With these 2 easy clicks, you’ve added the nofollow attribute to your link and removed the external link recommendation for search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not using AIOSEO yet? <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">Click here to get started today</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Have more questions about nofollow links and when to use them? Read on&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"why-are-nofollow-links-important\">Why Are Nofollow Links Important?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Above, we mentioned that nofollow links are important because links or backlinks are an important ranking factor.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>How does that work, exactly?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google considers links to be an important factor when deciding how to rank a website in search results. When you link to a website, it passes a small portion of your authority to it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That authority is commonly referred to by SEO experts as &#8220;link juice,&#8221; which is slang used to describe and measure how much power a backlink passes onto another site and therefore strengthens it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply put, if a website links to another website, search engines see this as a recommendation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, Google considers backlinks one of the strongest <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/seo-ranking-factors/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ranking factors</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sometimes you might want to link to a site without voting for it, or helping to increase that site&#8217;s rankings. In that case, you should use a nofollow link.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google will see the nofollow attribute on your link, and take that as a hint not to follow the link or consider it as a vote for that website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some SEO experts believe that making all external links nofollow can help your own website rank higher, though Google says that&#8217;s not the case.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more on how to optimize your site to rank higher, see our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"how-to-check-if-a-link-is-nofollow\">How to Check if a Link is Nofollow?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>How can you see if you&#8217;re looking at a follow or nofollow link? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This can be a bit tricky at first since follow and nofollow links look identical to the average web&nbsp;user. But there is a noticeable difference once you know what to look for.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To check if the nofollow tag is added to a link on a site, you need to hover on the link with your mouse, right click on it, and then select <strong>Inspect</strong> in your browser.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"380\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/find-nofollow-links.png\" alt=\"Add nofollow links in WordPress - how to check if a link is nofollow\" class=\"wp-image-21909\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/find-nofollow-links.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/find-nofollow-links-300x161.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/find-nofollow-links-704x380.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/find-nofollow-links-600x323.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Your browser window will now split into two parts, and in the Inspect panel, you’ll be able to see the HTML source code of the link, along with the nofollow attribute.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s show you the difference between follow vs. nofollow links in HTML code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Example of Follow Link:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><code>1</code></td><td><code>&lt;a href=\"https://aioseo.com\"&gt;the best seo plugin&lt;/a&gt;</code></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Example of Nofollow Link:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><code>1</code></td><td><code>&lt;a href=\"https://aioseo.com\" rel=\"nofollow\"&gt;the best seo plugin&lt;/a&gt;</code></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, the HTML code is identical, except for the addition of the rel=”nofollow” tag.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Need an easier way to quickly check follow vs. nofollow links?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google Chrome has an <a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/strike-out-nofollow-links/fkolbdohecbecliihaobiiamdmhhnaei\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">extension </a>that strikes out nofollow links. It&#8217;s a simple solution for checking if links are nofollow or not.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"when-should-you-add-nofollow-links\">Follow vs. Nofollow: When Should You Add Nofollow Links?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As a general <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">SEO best practice,</a> you should add nofollow links to all external websites that you don’t trust.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s completely acceptable and actually recommended to link to authority websites like Wikipedia, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">WPBeginner</a>, and New York Times without the nofollow attribute.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Linking to authority sites helps add credibility to your own website, which can improve rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, we recommend that you add the nofollow attribute to less credible websites that you don’t want to pass the link juice to.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This simply tells Google, “This link isn’t affiliated with my website. Please don’t crawl this link.”&nbsp; </p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you understand how to add nofollow links in WordPress in just 2 clicks. Make sure to follow these steps and your unfollow links are added in no time!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stay tuned for All in One SEO’s new features and improvements. And if you haven’t downloaded All in One SEO yet, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">what are you waiting for?&nbsp;</a></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-nofollow-links-in-wordpress/\">How to Add Nofollow Links in WordPress (In Just 2 Clicks)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-nofollow-links-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"How to Do an SEO Competitor Analysis [The Easy Way]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:136:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 03 Dec 2020 13:00:04 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"All in One SEO Pack\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"analyze competitor site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"SEO audit checklist\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"seo competitor analysis\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=21105\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:398:\"<p>Do you want to know how to do an SEO competitor analysis the easy way? In this post, you’ll learn how to do an SEO competitor analysis, but first, let’s explain what SEO competitor analysis means.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/\">How to Do an SEO Competitor Analysis [The Easy Way]</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22121:\"<p>Do you want to know how to do an SEO competitor analysis the easy way?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, you read it right! There’s an easy way to do this without needing to pay for expensive software to analyze your competition.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, you’ll learn how to analyze your competitors’ SEO with just a simple click. But first, let’s explain what SEO competitor analysis really means and how to first identify your competitors</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s a quick overview of what we’ll cover in this post. Simply click on these quick links to jump straight to different sections.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#why-do-you-need-an-seo-competitor-analysis\">Why Do You Need an SEO Competitor Analysis?</a></li><li><a href=\"#identify-your-competitors\">Identify Your Competitors</a></li><li><a href=\"#use-the-best-seo-competitor-analysis-tool\">Use the Best SEO Competitor Analysis Tool</a></li><li><a href=\"#analyze-competitor-site\">Analyze Competitor Site</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"why-do-you-need-an-seo-competitor-analysis\">Why Do You Need an SEO Competitor Analysis?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"409\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/why-you-need-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis-1.png\" alt=\"Why Do You Need an SEO Competitive Analysis?\" class=\"wp-image-21832\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/why-you-need-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/why-you-need-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis-1-300x168.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/why-you-need-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis-1-600x336.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO competitor analysis helps you know where you stand in relation to your competitors. It also works as a powerful research strategy in helping you to rank higher on SERPs, get more organic traffic, spend less on paid traffic, and earn more conversions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When analyzing what’s working for your competitors, you get insight into the strategies that are successful for others in your market and what keywords they are using.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And by finding the keywords that give your competitors the highest ROI (Return on Investment), you can use this information to improve your own SEO efforts and gain an edge.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In other words, your competitors’ keywords can be your greatest allies if you allow them. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more details on keywords and best SEO practices, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"identify-your-competitors\">Identify Your Competitors</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Before you do anything else, you first need to identify your main competitors. These are the websites that are competing for your desired keywords in organic search.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>How do you know who your competitors are? Let’s help you figure this out with 2 simple strategies.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><strong>Compile a List of Direct and Indirect Competitors</strong></li></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re already on the market, surely you know at least a few rivals that are competing with your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the other hand, if you just started your business, you probably had a few competitors in mind beforehand.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Compile a list of all direct and indirect competitors you can think of. This will be a solid start for your analysis.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"2\"><li><strong>Browse the Google Giant</strong></li></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>The next step is to browse the Google giant. Google has all the information you need to further identify your competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Type in your services, product, or brand keywords in Google and see what comes up. Pay extra attention to who’s ranking for the keywords relevant to what you do as a business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, if your business is selling auto parts online, then you can run a search on a keyword phrase such as “auto parts florida”.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"707\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/identify-your-competitors-google-search.png\" alt=\"Identify your competitors with a Google search\" class=\"wp-image-21801\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/identify-your-competitors-google-search.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/identify-your-competitors-google-search-300x291.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/identify-your-competitors-google-search-600x581.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can see websites that are ranking for this keyword phrase, and they would be your direct competition in terms of organic traffic (search traffic), as well as PPC (paid traffic from Google Ads).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Specifically, these are other businesses competing for the same customers as you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are other ways to identify your competitors, but these are the 2 easiest strategies to start with. Best of all, they don’t cost you anything.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s show you how to do an SEO competitor analysis the easy way using the most popular SEO plugin <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"use-the-best-seo-competitor-analysis-tool\">Use the Best SEO Competitor Analysis Tool</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is the most powerful and user-friendly WordPress SEO plugin in the market. It lets you analyze your website in seconds. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO, you can:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Follow our SEO Audit Checklist to optimize your website’s settings</li><li>Identify any critical errors that could be harming your rankings</li><li>Review recommended SEO improvements</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>There is a reason 2,000,000+ professionals use AIOSEO to improve their website search rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, the first thing you need to do is install and activate the AIOSEO plugin. For more details, see our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\">All in One SEO installation guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"431\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-new-dashboard.png\" alt=\"WordPress Tutorials, Tips, and Resources to Help Grow Your Business How to Do an SEO Competitor Analysis [The Easy Way]\" class=\"wp-image-21802\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-new-dashboard.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-new-dashboard-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-new-dashboard-600x354.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’ve never installed a plugin before, you can find a step by step guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin on WPBeginner</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t forget to enter the license key if you’re using the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Pro version</a>. Activating the Pro version will automatically import all SEO data and configuration settings from the free version with no data loss.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once AIOSEO is installed, you simply visit the <strong>All in One SEO » SEO Analysis </strong>page to check out a quick overview of your AIOSEO dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"439\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/All-in-One-SEO-Analysis.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO SEO Audit Checklist\" class=\"wp-image-21803\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/All-in-One-SEO-Analysis.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/All-in-One-SEO-Analysis-300x180.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/All-in-One-SEO-Analysis-600x361.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will take you to the <strong>SEO Audit Checklist </strong>page, where you can see your overall site score. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"556\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-overall-site-score.png\" alt=\"SEO Competitor Analysis- SEO Audit Checklist\" class=\"wp-image-21805\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-overall-site-score.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-overall-site-score-300x228.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-overall-site-score-600x457.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The overall site score tells you how well you have optimized your website, and you can target critical issues and warnings with AIOSEO’s site analysis feature.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The general rule of thumb is to aim for a score of 60 and above. If you end up with a low score, you can learn how to improve your score in our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide.</a> </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"analyze-competitor-site\">Analyze Competitor Site</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>But for now, we’ll focus on analyzing your competitors’ SEO so that you can find their weaknesses, as well as their strengths, and capitalize on them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While in the SEO Audit Checklist, you click on <strong>Analyze Competitor Site</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"556\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site.png\" alt=\"SEO Competitor Analysis - Analyze Competitor Site\" class=\"wp-image-21806\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site-300x228.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site-600x457.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, enter your competitor’s website URL in the window, and press on the <strong>Analyze </strong>button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"542\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-analyze-competitor-site.png\" alt=\"SEO Competitor Analysis - Analyze Competitor Site \" class=\"wp-image-21807\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-analyze-competitor-site.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-analyze-competitor-site-300x223.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-analyze-competitor-site-600x445.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, you’ll see your competitor’s SEO analysis appear in the same window, and you can compare important metrics, like page title, keywords, description, and page load speed.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s dig a bit deeper into a few of these metrics.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"preview-snippet-and-keywords\">Preview Snippet and Keywords</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Analyze Competitor Site page also shows you a preview snippet of the title and keywords of which your competitor has optimized their site.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"269\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-preview-snippet-and-keywords.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO Preview Snippet and Keywords\" class=\"wp-image-21812\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-preview-snippet-and-keywords.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-preview-snippet-and-keywords-300x111.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-preview-snippet-and-keywords-600x221.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Go ahead and compare it with your site&#8217;s SEO. It can give you important clues on what you need to improve to rank higher on SERPs and earn more conversions.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"basic-seo\">Basic SEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the <strong>Basic SEO</strong> section, you can see the title and description and their respective character length, keywords that were found in the title and description, H1 tag, H2 tags, image alt attributes, and external links.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"574\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo.png\" alt=\"SEO Competitor Analysis - Basic SEO\" class=\"wp-image-21814\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo-300x236.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo-600x472.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You should always use your focus keyword in both title and description to let search engines and other crawlers know what your site or page is about. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Having said that, you can view this hard data in Basic SEO and utilize the information to improve your own SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"574\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo-critical-issues.png\" alt=\"SEO Competitor Analysis - Basic SEO Critical Issues\" class=\"wp-image-21817\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo-critical-issues.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo-critical-issues-300x236.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/seo-competitor-analysis-basic-seo-critical-issues-600x472.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, there are some images on this page that have no alt attribute. Alt attributes help search engines understand what an image is about, which is important for overall SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more details, please visit WPBeginner’s post on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/image-alt-text-vs-image-title-in-wordpress-whats-the-difference/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">the difference between alt text and image titles</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"advanced-seo\">Advanced SEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the <strong>Advanced SEO </strong>section, you can see if the site is using the canonical link tag. Meaning if they have specified a canonical URL for each post to avoid duplicate content penalty from Google.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"502\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo.png\" alt=\"SEO Competitor Analysis - Advanced SEO\" class=\"wp-image-21818\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo-300x206.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo-600x413.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Equally important, you can also see information about <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-stop-search-engines-from-crawling-a-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">noindex header or meta tag</a>, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/www-vs-non-www-which-is-better-for-wordpress-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">www and non-www URL redirects</a>, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/glossary/robots-txt/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">robots.txt file</a>, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-themes/how-to-add-facebook-open-graph-meta-data-in-wordpress-themes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Open Graph meta tags</a>, and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/a-guide-to-schema-org-markup-for-rich-snippets/\">Schema.org data</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"502\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo-critical-issues.png\" alt=\"SEO Competitor Analysis - Advanced SEO Critical Issues\" class=\"wp-image-21819\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo-critical-issues.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo-critical-issues-300x206.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-advanced-seo-critical-issues-600x413.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can see that this page has 2 critical advanced SEO issues. In this instance, the robots.txt file is missing (a text file that allows a website to provide instructions to web crawling bots) and Open Graph meta tags (they help social media websites get meta data about your posts pages) are also missing.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"performance\">Performance</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the most crucial factors for SEO is how fast your website is loading, i.e. the response time. You can view this information in <strong>Performance</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"625\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site-performance.png\" alt=\"SEO Competitor Analysis - Performance \" class=\"wp-image-21821\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site-performance.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site-performance-300x257.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site-performance-600x514.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Why is response time or page load speed a crucial aspect for SEO?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The simple answer is that Google and other search engines penalize sites that load slowly, and it also affects the user experience. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Research has shown that if a page takes longer than 3 seconds to load, over a quarter of users will click away, which significantly increases bounce rate and lower conversions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">AIOSEO</a> makes this a simple fix and even suggests response time improvements.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more details, please visit WPBeginner’s post on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-performance-speed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to boost WordPress speed and performance. </a></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"625\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site-performance-critical-issues.png\" alt=\"SEO Competitor Analysis - Performance Critical Issues\" class=\"wp-image-21822\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site-performance-critical-issues.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site-performance-critical-issues-300x257.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-analyze-competitor-site-performance-critical-issues-600x514.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In this case, there are 4 critical performance issues to consider for optimal performance, and if you make sure your website doesn’t have any of these, you’ll gain a big advantage over your competitor.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"recommended-improvements\">Recommended Improvements</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, you can scroll down and look for <strong>Recommended Improvements</strong>, which shows how your competitor can improve their overall score and ranking. Take advantage of this information and compare it with your site&#8217;s SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"493\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-recommended-improvements.png\" alt=\"SEO Competitor Analysis - Recommended Improvements\" class=\"wp-image-21823\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-recommended-improvements.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-recommended-improvements-300x203.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-competitor-analysis-recommended-improvements-600x405.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, there are 2 recommended improvements, and they are both security related.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With an SEO competitor analysis, you&#8217;ll get lots of valuable data that you can use to improve your own SEO efforts and gain an edge over your competitors. It will help you rank higher on SERPs, get more organic traffic, and earn conversions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Depending on the size of your website and the number of active competitors, you’ll want to rerun a competitor analysis every 6 months. We recommend that you keep an eye on changes your competitors are making, so you can react to their strategies quickly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you understand how to do an SEO competitor analysis the easy way. Make sure to analyze every SEO metric, and with a little bit of work, you can pass your competitors’ SEO at rocket speed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thank you, as always, for supporting the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">best SEO plugin for WordPress</a>!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stay tuned for more updates, since we have lots of amazing new features planned for you soon.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not using All in One SEO yet? What are you waiting for?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Click here to get started with All in One SEO today!</a></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/\">How to Do an SEO Competitor Analysis [The Easy Way]</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"Ultimate WordPress SEO Guide: Optimize Your Site in 2020\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:120:\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 14 Nov 2020 13:53:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=18643\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:355:\"<p>Want to learn how to optimize your site with WordPress SEO, but don’t know how to get started? Follow our ultimate WordPress SEO guide to get maximum traffic!</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">Ultimate WordPress SEO Guide: Optimize Your Site in 2020</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Keri Engel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29442:\"<p>Want to learn how to optimize your site with WordPress SEO, but don’t know how to get started?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’re here to help you out!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As one of the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">best SEO plugins</a>, we know what it takes certain websites to rank better than the others on search results. In this post, you’ll learn the best WordPress SEO tips and tricks to optimize your website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, this guide covers all the details about WordPress SEO, step by step.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Feel free to use our table of contents below to navigate through this jam-packed WordPress SEO guide.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#what-is-seo\">What is SEO?</a></li><li><a href=\"#wordpress-seo-basics\">Getting the WordPress SEO Basics Down</a></li><li><a href=\"#best-wordpress-seo-plugin\">Use the Best WordPress SEO Plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#optimize-blog-posts\">How to Optimize Your Blog Posts</a></li><li><a href=\"#bonus-seo-tips\">Bonus WordPress SEO Tips</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get started with the basics: what is SEO, and why is it important?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-is-seo\">What Is SEO?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO or Search Engine Optimization is a practice of optimizing your web pages in order to drive free organic traffic from search engines like Google. With SEO, your goal is to follow WordPress SEO best practices on your site, so you can help search engines easily discover your content and display it in the search results.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are 3 things search engines do in order to find and display your content to its users:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Crawling</strong>: Discover content on the internet by scanning each URL they find</li><li><strong>Indexing</strong>: Organize the content they found during crawling, so they can quickly list it in search results for relevant queries</li><li><strong>Ranking</strong>: Ordering the indexed content in search results such a way that the most relevant content appears at the top</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>On a daily basis, Google processes over <a href=\"https://www.internetlivestats.com/google-search-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">3.5 billion searches</a>&#8230; Imagine how much more traffic you could get with a high ranking!&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To put it simply, SEO brings your website to life. Sure, it’s not an overnight strategy, but the results are worth it.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not to mention, there are guides out there (like this one) to jumpstart your WordPress SEO strategy.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"wordpress-seo-basics\">Getting the WordPress SEO Basics Down&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Before you get started, make sure your website is set up for SEO. The next 4 questions will kick everything into gear.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Is Your Website Indexed?&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first thing you need to do is to ensure your website can indexed by search engines.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can think of “index” as another word for database. When Google indexes a website, they input that site’s information into their database.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If your website isn’t in their database, users won’t find your website over search. It’s critical to make sure your site is indexed.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see if your site allows indexing on your WP dashboard. Head to Head to <strong>Settings » Reading </strong>on your dashboard.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-visibility-settings.png\" alt=\"wordpress seo visibility settings\" class=\"wp-image-20048\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Uncheck the box next to <strong>Search engine visibility</strong> to allow indexing.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Is Your Website WWW or non-WWW?&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Wait… you can choose if your website URL has WWW or not?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s right. Your site address will look like one of the following:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>https://</em><strong><em>www.</em></strong><em>samplewebsite.com or http://samplewebsite.com&nbsp;</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google will only identify <strong>one </strong>of these URLs as your website—you can’t choose both.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On another note, there’s a lot of talk about which URL is better&#8230; <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/www-vs-non-www-which-is-better-for-wordpress-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Is WWW better than non-WWW?&nbsp;</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>It doesn’t matter which one you choose. However, once you do, choose your site address, stick with it. Like we mentioned earlier, Google identifies one site address only.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fortunately, with WordPress, it’s easy to set your URL preference by naviagating to <strong>Settings » General</strong>. Then insert your preferred URL in both WordPress Address (URL) and Site Address (URL).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-site-url-settings.png\" alt=\"wordpress URL settings\" class=\"wp-image-20052\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Are Your WordPress URLs SEO-friendly?&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An SEO-friendly URL looks something like below:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>http:&#47;&#47;www.example.com/how-to-make-a-website</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>This URL is short, organized, and easy to read. Search engines and online users can tell what this webpage is about—how to make a website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Unoptimized URLs, on the other hand, are disorganized and long. They usually include numbers, letters, and special characters.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>https:&#47;&#47;www.example.com/?p=10467X&amp;UKEwiv9vuz1tXsAhU</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>To make sure your URLs are SEO friendly, head to <strong>Settings</strong> » <strong>Permalinks </strong>and <strong>Post name.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-seo-friendly-permalinks.png\" alt=\"wordpress seo friendly permalinks\" class=\"wp-image-20053\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This URL structure is SEO friendly in most cases, but it doesn’t apply to every website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, a news publication site might need a URL with the day and name. Or, a large site with hundreds of articles might need a custom structure.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can check out this article to find the <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/seo-friendly-url-structure-for-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">best URL structure </a>for your business.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Is Your Website Secure?&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Website security has always been a top priority for Google. They also want to ensure that websites people access from Google are also secure and protect users’ privacy.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that’s why Google recommends implementing SSL / HTTPS on all websites.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SSL is an industry standard security measure that creates an encrypted link between each visitor’s browser and your website. This adds an additional security layer to your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you install SSL on your site, a padlock sign will appear in the address bar, showing your visitors that they’re on a secure page. In addition, your website address will begin with HTTPS instead of just HTTP.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-ssl-https.png\" alt=\"wordpress ssl https for seo\" class=\"wp-image-20055\"/></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>MonsterInsights, for example, has a lock next to their URL and an ‘s’ after HTTP. This means their site is encrypted.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, when an online user logs into your site or buys a product, the SSL certificate will better protect their information.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can get a <strong>free </strong>SSL certificate through a <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">WordPress hosting site</a> or <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-get-a-free-ssl-certificate-for-your-wordpress-website/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">WordPress SSL plugin.</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also check out this post to learn more about <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/does-https-keep-wordpress-secure/\">keeping WordPress secure</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"best-wordpress-seo-plugin\">Use the Best WordPress SEO Plugin&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress SEO can get overwhelming, especially in the beginning. Luckily, you can manage this strategy with a plugin. An SEO plugin helps optimize your site with user-friendly features.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So which SEO plugin should you use?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">All in One SEO</a>!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All in One SEO is the original SEO plugin for WordPress, which has been used over 2 million websites around the globe.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With All in One SEO, you can easily implement on page SEO optimization, like adding meta title and description. A few more benefits of the plugin are:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Generate a sitemap automatically and generate it to popular search engines</li><li>Provide complete support for Google Knowledge Graph and Schema.org snippets</li><li>Easily implement Google AMP SEO</li><li>Add advanced eCommerce SEO support for WooCommerce</li><li>And more</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Put simply, All in One SEO takes care of all the technical SEO optimization you need for your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Generate Your XML Sitemap&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An XML sitemap is a list of every important URL on your site. When you submit a sitemap, Google can understand and index your content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you don’t upload an XML sitemap, Google will have trouble identifying your webpages.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With All in One SEO, you can easily create your sitemap and send it to all popular search engines. To generate a sitemap, go to<strong> All in One SEO » Sitemaps</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-sitemap-generator.png\" alt=\"wordpress sitemap generator\" class=\"wp-image-20056\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you scroll down, you’ll notice a list of<strong> Sitemap settings</strong>. These settings let you choose what pages you’d like to add.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-sitemap-settings.png\" alt=\"wordpress sitemap settings\" class=\"wp-image-20057\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure to toggle on <strong>Enable Sitemap Indexes</strong> option.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more details, check out our article on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-xml-sitemaps-vs-all-in-one-seo-sitemaps/\">XML sitemaps vs. All in One SEO</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"optimize-blog-posts\">How to Optimize Your Blog Posts</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know how to configure the basic WordPress SEO settings, it’s time to learn how to optimize your posts for SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Keyword Research&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Keyword research is a crucial part of SEO. It’s the practice of identifying the terms that people enter into search engines so you can use them in your posts.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Keywords are an important Google ranking factor that determines whether or not your post show up in search results.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, how do you do keyword research? There are a lot of different factors to consider:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Relevancy</strong> &#8211; Make sure to choose the keywords that are most relevant to the content you&#8217;re providing</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>High search volume</strong> &#8211; Choose the keywords that most people are likely to use&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Competition</strong> &#8211; Ideally, you need to use low competition keywords, so you can easily rank your content for them</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We suggest using <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-do-keyword-research-for-your-wordpress-blog/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">keyword search tools</a> to find useful and high volume keywords for your audience. You can also read more about <a href=\"https://www.blogtyrant.com/how-to-easily-find-the-best-keywords/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to do keyword research.</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Add Internal Links&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Internal linking is simply linking one page to another page on your site. We call these links “internal” because they’re within your website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So why are internal links SEO friendly?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>They keep readers interested</strong> &#8211;&nbsp; When a user reads your blog post, they can click on an internal link to read another blog post, and so on.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, let’s say you write a guide about plant health. You could add internal links to other posts about house plants, outdoor plants, and trees.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A reader might think, “Wow! There’s so much information about plant health. I don’t need to go to another source, this website has everything I need.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When readers are engaged with your content, it can increase your authority and rankings.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>They improve site navigation</strong> &#8211; Internal links help your readers and Google navigate your site. Google, specifically, has an easier time identifying and ranking your posts for search.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add an internal link, head to your blog post. Highlight the word you want to link and click on the<strong> link</strong> icon.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-internal-links.png\" alt=\"internal linking for wordpress seo\" class=\"wp-image-20058\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Type in a blog post you’d like to link and hit enter.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-insert-link.png\" alt=\"insert link in wordpress\" class=\"wp-image-20059\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way to improve blog post navigation is with anchor links. Anchor links let readers jump around your page. This is especially important for long articles.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Anchor links are commonly used to link a table of contents to the post’s headings and subheadings. This post will teach you <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-easily-add-anchor-links-in-wordpress-step-by-step/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to add anchor links.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Edit External Links&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s common to add external links within your content. Websites externally link to other sites for a few reasons:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Research&nbsp;</li><li>Affiliate partners&nbsp;</li><li>Recommendations&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Linking to valuable sources can make your content more credible. But here’s the thing about external links.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When search engines identify them on your website, they can pass some of your <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/glossary/backlinks/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">link authority</a> over to those external links.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, when you link to an outside source and you don’t want to pass the link juice, then add <strong>nofollow</strong>. This tells Google, “This link isn’t affiliated with my website. Please don’t crawl this link.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can add nofollow to your external links with All in One SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Head to your blog post editing page. Select the block containing your link and hit the <strong>link</strong> icon. Once you insert your external link, click <strong>Add “nofollow” link</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-nofollow-link.png\" alt=\"add nofollow link in wordpress\" class=\"wp-image-20061\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Optimize Images&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>While images are a great addition to your content, they can slow down your site. You can avoid this with compressed, high-quality images.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you compress a photo, it shrinks its image files without taking away the quality. We suggest <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/speed-wordpress-save-images-optimized-web/#best-image-optimization-tools\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">compressing images</a> before uploading them to WordPress.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Along with compressing images, you should also add a title and alt text to photos. Alt text stands for “alternative text.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The alt text and title help Google understand what your images are. This is also a helpful tool for someone with vision loss.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can add alt text and a title to each image you upload to WordPress.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-image-seo-optimization.png\" alt=\"boost your image seo with alt text and title text\" class=\"wp-image-20064\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Try to add alt text and a title to each image you upload. If it makes sense, you can add keywords to rank your photos.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Add Categories and Tags&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Organized content is easy to navigate—categories and tags help with that. Before we explain how categories and tags affect SEO, let’s explain what they are.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ll start with categories. Categories organize your posts by topic. For example, let&#8217;s say you own a Spain travel blog.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some categories you might have are:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Spanish cuisine</li><li>Drinks</li><li>Sightseeing&nbsp;</li><li>Getting around&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also think of categories as the chapters of a book—each chapter covers a broad topic. In WordPress, every post must be categorized, or else it’ll be labeled as “uncategorized.”&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now let’s talk about tags. While categories group your blog posts into broad topics, tags describe each blog post with 1 or 2 keywords.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s go back to the Spain travel blog example.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some tags you might add to blog posts about “Sightseeing” are:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Architecture&nbsp;</li><li>Statues&nbsp;</li><li>Nature&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>See how these tags specify the category, sightseeing? So, if you write an article about Spain’s beaches, you would add “Sightseeing” as the category and “Nature” as the tag.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So how do categories and tags improve WordPress SEO?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like internal links, categories and tags improve your site navigation. Readers and Google have an easier time going through your blog posts when they’re organized.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can optimize your categories and tags with <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-wordpress-categories-and-tags-in-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">MonsterInsights’ category and tag tracker.</a> This tool analyzes which categories and tags get the most traffic.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t know how to add categories and tags to your post? You can read our guide: <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-categories-and-tags-work/\">How WordPress Categories and Tags Work.&nbsp;</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Optimize for Search Results&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that your content is SEO-friendly, you can optimize it for search results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is one of the best ways to improve clickthroughs of your content in the results, so you can possibly drive more traffic.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>From your post or page editor, scroll down until you see <strong>AIOSEO Settings</strong>. Enter the title of your blog post under<strong> Post Title.</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-title-tags-meta-description.png\" alt=\"wordpress title tags meta description\" class=\"wp-image-20065\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO will calculate how long your title tag is. It shouldn’t be any longer than 60 characters.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next is your <strong>meta description</strong>. Your meta description summarizes your content on search engines. All in One SEO suggests keeping your meta description at 160 characters or less.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-meta-description.png\" alt=\"wordpress meta description\" class=\"wp-image-20066\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Last are your<strong> keywords</strong>. When you enter your primary and secondary keywords, AIOSEO will evaluate how well they’re placed.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It can also analyze your on-page SEO—content length, internal links, and external links are a few examples.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-on-page-seo-analysis.png\" alt=\"wordpress on-page seo analysis\" class=\"wp-image-20067\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, would you look at that&#8230;your content is officially WordPress SEO ready!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Respond to Comments&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s always encouraging to receive comments from your readers&#8230;But sometimes it can get out of hand.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First things first, get rid of spam comments. Spam comments take up space and add no value to your content. Plus, spam comments used to have bad links, which could sabotage your authority and negatively impacts SEO.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A spam filtering service like <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/akismet-101-guide-for-all-wordpress-users/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Akismet</a> will keep those comments out of your site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whew, that was an easy fix. But here’s another problem you may come across—a LOT of comments.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While blog post comments boost WordPress SEO (and make you feel good), they can also slow down your site speed.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If this is the case, you’ll have to split your comments into different pages. This post will help you <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-paginate-comments-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">paginate comments</a>, step by step.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"bonus-seo-tips\">3 Bonus WordPress SEO Tips&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Want to learn even MORE about WordPress SEO? You’re in the right place. Here are 3 additional tips to boost your WordPress SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Analyze Your Site&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You won’t know how your WordPress SEO is doing without analyzing your site. You can target critical issues and warnings with AIOSEO’s site analysis feature.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Under <strong>All in One SEO</strong>, click on <strong>SEO Analysis.</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-seo-audit.png\" alt=\"wordpress seo audit\" class=\"wp-image-20068\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>From here, you can check your SEO site score. The general rule of thumb is to aim for a score of 60 and above. If you end up with a low score, then scroll down and look for the recommendation to improve your overall score and ranking.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/seo-site-analysis.png\" alt=\"wordpress seo site analysis\" class=\"wp-image-20069\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, from the above screenshot, it looks like this website is missing some critical areas of basic SEO. Now that we know these problems, we can fix them and raise our SEO score.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On another note, you can also analyze competitor sites. Click on <strong>Analyze competitor site</strong> and enter their URL.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/seo-competitor-analysis.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-20070\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>From here, you can compare important metrics, like keywords and site loading time.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Along with AIOSEO, you should also use <a href=\"https://search.google.com/search-console/about\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google Search Console</a> and <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">MonsterInsights</a> to analyze organic traffic.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can learn more about using MonsterInsights with this guide: <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">How to add Google Analytics the right way.&nbsp;</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Add Schema&nbsp;Markup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Schema markup is code that you put on your website to help the search engines return more informative results for users. With schema markup, you can add rich snippets to your search results, which could improve your organic traffic</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example… have you ever seen search results that look like this?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/schema-rich-snippets.png\" alt=\"wordpress schema rich snippets\" class=\"wp-image-20071\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Or maybe this?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/review-schema-rich-snippets.png\" alt=\"review schema rich snippets\" class=\"wp-image-20072\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These are 2 examples of <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/rich-snippets-schema/\">schema markup</a>. Without a doubt, schema markup reveals more information about the page than a typical search snippet, which helps your business stand out from other search results and also boost organic traffic.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add schema, click on <strong>Search Appearance</strong> under <strong>All in One SEO</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-schema-markup-1.png\" alt=\"wordpress schema markup settings\" class=\"wp-image-20073\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then, scroll down to Schema Markup.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Enter your business’ information to add schema markup on Google. If you’re a local business, you can add local schema with our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/local-seo/\">local SEO feature</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Optimize Your Social Sharing&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve probably shared a blog post on Twitter or Facebook at least once. When you share a blog post, something like below pops up.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-social-media-optimization.png\" alt=\"wordpress social seo\n\" class=\"wp-image-20074\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Notice how the headline, description, and featured image are ready to share? This didn’t happen by accident—Smash Balloon optimized their social settings.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing your social settings does 2 things:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>It makes it easy to share </strong>&#8211; With everything ready to go, all users have to do is click “share.”&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Keywords and alt text</strong> &#8211; You can add your keywords and alt text to the image, title, and description for extra optimization.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO, you can set up Facebook and Twitter sharing. On your blog post editing page, head back to AIOSEO settings and click on <strong>Social.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-seo-social-setting.png\" alt=\"social settings\" class=\"wp-image-20075\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you scroll down, edit your title, description, and media. We recommend using relevant keywords and alt text to optimize the post.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/wordpress-seo-social-settings.png\" alt=\"wordpress seo social settings\" class=\"wp-image-20076\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now your blog post is ready for social sharing. You can add social sharing buttons to your blog with this post: <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-add-social-share-buttons-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">How to add social share buttons.</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that’s all!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you understand what WordPress SEO is and how to get started. Make sure to follow every step, and your WordPress SEO will be optimized in no time!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stay tuned for All in One SEO’s new features and improvements. And if you haven’t downloaded All in One SEO yet, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">what are you waiting for?</a>&nbsp;</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">Ultimate WordPress SEO Guide: Optimize Your Site in 2020</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"All in One SEO 4.0 Is Coming Soon! Here’s Your Sneak Peek…\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:146:\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-4-0-coming-soon-sneak-peek/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=all-in-one-seo-4-0-coming-soon-sneak-peek\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-4-0-coming-soon-sneak-peek/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 11 Nov 2020 16:24:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=18505\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:361:\"<p>We’re ready to revolutionize WordPress SEO - are you ready to join us? See all the groundbreaking features coming out soon in All in One SEO 4.0.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-4-0-coming-soon-sneak-peek/\">All in One SEO 4.0 Is Coming Soon! Here’s Your Sneak Peek…</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Keri Engel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10478:\"<p>Earlier this year, we announced that All in One SEO joined the Awesome Motive family.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With over 2 million active installs, All in One SEO is one of the most popular and reliable WordPress SEO plugins in the world &#8211; and we want to make it even better.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Our goal:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To <strong>make SEO easy for everyone</strong> by not only giving you the right tools, but also actionable insights to optimize your site, even if you’re not an SEO expert.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the past few months, we’ve released several new features including:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Image SEO addon</li><li>Breadcrumbs</li><li>Google News sitemaps</li><li>Local SEO addon</li><li>RSS feed footer</li><li>Site Health Checks</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>But we’ve only just been getting warmed up&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve also secretly been working on a MASSIVE update to lay the groundwork to make AIOSEO the most innovative SEO plugin on the market.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s been hard to keep this a secret because we’re incredibly excited for you to use this tool to get more traffic than ever.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, we can’t wait any longer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that we’re getting closer and closer to our release date, we wanted to give you a sneak peek of what’s in store.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s take a look…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>All in One SEO 4.0 &#8211; A New Way Forward</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To help make SEO easier for everyone, and lay the groundwork for even more innovative features, <strong>we’ve completely redesigned All in One SEO from the ground up</strong> to be ultra user-friendly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the process, we also significantly improved performance so AIOSEO is <strong>faster than ever</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The most noticeable change when you update will be AIOSEO’s new look:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"472\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-new-dashboard.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO new dashboard\" class=\"wp-image-18507\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-new-dashboard.png 800w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-new-dashboard-600x354.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-new-dashboard-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-new-dashboard-768x453.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-new-dashboard-424x250.png 424w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-new-dashboard-100x59.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-new-dashboard-150x89.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-new-dashboard-200x118.png 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-new-dashboard-450x266.png 450w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Right away, you&#8217;ll notice a few things:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>All in One SEO Menu Location Change</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The All in One SEO menu has moved beneath the &#8220;Settings&#8221; in your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We made this menu change to follow WordPress plugin development best practices.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s because with AIOSEO 4.0 we’re improving not just the look of the plugin, but everything under the hood to make sure our code is up to date, runs smoothly, and is easy to extend and add new features to.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>New Setup Wizard</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step in setting up All in One SEO is going through the setup wizard. Now it’s easier than ever to customize your settings to fit your site with just a few clicks.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-setup-wizard.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO new setup wizard\" class=\"wp-image-18510\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-setup-wizard.png 800w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-setup-wizard-600x362.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-setup-wizard-300x181.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-setup-wizard-768x463.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-setup-wizard-415x250.png 415w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-setup-wizard-100x60.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-setup-wizard-150x90.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-setup-wizard-200x121.png 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-setup-wizard-450x271.png 450w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>New Dashboard</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, the new dashboard itself is a huge change!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While we&#8217;ve added several new features, don&#8217;t worry &#8211; all the features you know and love are still here &#8211; just easier to use.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new dashboard includes important notifications, guides so you can easily get help, quick links to the most important settings, and best of all…</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;our brand new SEO Site Score!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>NEW SEO Site Score</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"731\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score-1024x731.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-18512\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score-1024x731.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score-600x429.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score-300x214.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score-768x548.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score-350x250.png 350w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score-100x71.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score-150x107.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score-200x143.png 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score-450x321.png 450w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score-900x643.png 900w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-site-score.png 1277w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With the new Site Score and SEO Audit Checklist, you can analyze your entire WordPress site to detect critical errors and get actionable insights to boost your SEO and get more traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>SEO Competitor Analysis</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Notice something else in that screenshot above?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s right, AIOSEO 4.0 now includes a competitor analysis tool:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"594\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-competitor-analysis.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-18513\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-competitor-analysis.png 800w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-competitor-analysis-600x446.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-competitor-analysis-300x223.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-competitor-analysis-768x570.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-competitor-analysis-337x250.png 337w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-competitor-analysis-100x74.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-competitor-analysis-150x111.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-competitor-analysis-200x149.png 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-competitor-analysis-450x334.png 450w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now there&#8217;s no need to pay for expensive software to analyze the competition &#8211; we&#8217;re bringing it right to your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>TruSEO On-Page Analysis</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing each page and blog post to rank high in search results can be difficult and time-consuming when you&#8217;re not an SEO expert.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s why we&#8217;ve also included a new <strong>TruSEO Score</strong> to tell you exactly how to optimize each piece of content.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"880\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-truseo-keyword.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-18515\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-truseo-keyword.png 880w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-truseo-keyword-600x364.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-truseo-keyword-300x182.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-truseo-keyword-768x466.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-truseo-keyword-412x250.png 412w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-truseo-keyword-100x61.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-truseo-keyword-150x91.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-truseo-keyword-200x121.png 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/aioseo-truseo-keyword-450x273.png 450w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Instead of just a pass or fail, you&#8217;ll get a score out of 100 and a detailed analysis and to-do list.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>And More…</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s not all!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All in One SEO includes all the features you&#8217;re already using, plus even more:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Customizable access control</li><li>Easy settings importer/exporter</li><li>1-click migration from other SEO plugins</li><li>&#8230;and more</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>All in One SEO 4.0 will be released very, very soon, so <strong>keep an eye on your WordPress dashboard for the update prompt</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’re not stopping here…&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With our redesign nearly complete, we can turn our focus to new features.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, we already have some amazing new features in store for you to help you rank higher than ever.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>No need to spend hours studying SEO or buy expensive software.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’re ready to revolutionize WordPress SEO &#8211; are you ready to join us?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re not using AIOSEO yet, what are you waiting for?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-pro-version/\">Click here to get started with All in One SEO today!</a><br></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-4-0-coming-soon-sneak-peek/\">All in One SEO 4.0 Is Coming Soon! Here’s Your Sneak Peek…</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-4-0-coming-soon-sneak-peek/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"37\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"Introducing Site Health Checks for All in One SEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:124:\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-site-health-checks/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=introducing-site-health-checks\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-site-health-checks/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 24 Sep 2020 13:44:10 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"site health\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"site health checks\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=16645\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:553:\"<p>Are all your SEO settings optimized to unlock the highest rankings and traffic? Now it&#8217;s easier than ever to find out. With our latest update, All in One SEO now seamlessly integrates with the WordPress Site Health tool to ensure&#8201;&#8230;&#8201;<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-site-health-checks/\" class=\"excerpt-more-link\">Continue reading</a></p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-site-health-checks/\">Introducing Site Health Checks for All in One SEO</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Keri Engel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3533:\"<p>Are all your SEO settings optimized to unlock the highest rankings and traffic?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now it&#8217;s easier than ever to find out.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With our latest update, All in One SEO now seamlessly integrates with the WordPress Site Health tool to ensure your setup is complete and your site is ready to rank in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s how it works…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>WordPress Site Health + All in One SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that WordPress has a built-in feature called &#8220;<a aria-label=\"Site Health (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/tips-to-get-a-100-in-wordpress-site-health-check-score/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Site Health</a>&#8221; under the Tools menu?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This tool helps you to monitor your site and lets you know about any critical errors or potential issues, so you can make sure everything’s running smoothly.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"831\" height=\"762\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/aioseo-site-health-checks.png\" alt=\"All in One SEO Site Health Checks\" class=\"wp-image-16646\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/aioseo-site-health-checks.png 831w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/aioseo-site-health-checks-600x550.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/aioseo-site-health-checks-300x275.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/aioseo-site-health-checks-768x704.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/aioseo-site-health-checks-273x250.png 273w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/aioseo-site-health-checks-100x92.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/aioseo-site-health-checks-150x138.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/aioseo-site-health-checks-200x183.png 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/aioseo-site-health-checks-450x413.png 450w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All in One SEO Site Health checks will now monitor:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Indexability</strong>: Make sure your site is public and ready to be crawled by search engine bots.</li><li><strong>Basic Site Settings</strong>: Checks if the Site Title or Tagline are set, so you never have a blank title tag.</li><li><strong>Schema Settings</strong>: Ensure your markup is valid and all the required info is filled out.</li><li><strong>Noindex Monitoring</strong>: You also get a list of the types of content (post types, taxonomies, etc.) that are noindexed/nofollowed under the Site Health Info tab as a reminder.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>With this release, we’ve also included several small fixes and improvements to make sure your site keeps running smoothly and ranking for all your target keywords.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see a complete list of all the changes and improvements in the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-changelog/\">changelog</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thank you, as always, for supporting the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">best SEO plugin for WordPress</a>!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stay tuned for more updates, since we have lots of amazing new features planned for you soon.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not using All in One SEO yet? What are you waiting for?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-pro-version/\">Click here to get started with All in One SEO today</a>!</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-site-health-checks/\">Introducing Site Health Checks for All in One SEO</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-site-health-checks/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"5\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"Announcing All in One SEO 3.7: Control Your RSS Feed Footer in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:140:\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-all-in-one-seo-3-7-rss-feed/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=announcing-all-in-one-seo-3-7-rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-all-in-one-seo-3-7-rss-feed/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 20 Aug 2020 16:44:43 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"rss\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=15154\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:605:\"<p>Ever felt frustrated because you spent a lot of time writing original content… &#8230;only to see it being republished on spam sites that don’t link back to you? Sometimes, the website with stolen content even outranks the original post. Yikes.&#8201;&#8230;&#8201;<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-all-in-one-seo-3-7-rss-feed/\" class=\"excerpt-more-link\">Continue reading</a></p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-all-in-one-seo-3-7-rss-feed/\">Announcing All in One SEO 3.7: Control Your RSS Feed Footer in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Keri Engel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4290:\"<p>Ever felt frustrated because you spent a lot of time writing original content…</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;only to see it being republished on spam sites that don’t link back to you?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sometimes, the website with stolen content even outranks the original post. Yikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We feel your pain.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s why with the latest release of All in One SEO, now you can add a bit of content to the beginning and end of your posts in your RSS feed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With this feature, you can easily add credits, custom text and links, or even advertisements to help monetize your blog.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s take a closer look…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why Add Content to Your RSS Feed?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>First things first: what’s RSS? And how important is it to your content marketing?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>RSS (Really Simple Syndication) is a type of web feed that automatically gets updated whenever you publish content on your site. RSS can help you expose your brand to more people by distributing it to more websites.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The problem is when other websites steal your content and don’t link back to your original post. These sites are called <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/beginners-guide-to-preventing-blog-content-scraping-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">content scrapers</a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Since content scrapers re-publish your posts and don’t even link back to you, Google doesn’t know you’re the original owner of your content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s the good news: All in One SEO 3.7’s RSS Content Feature allows you to <strong>add links to your posts</strong> <strong>in your RSS feed</strong>&#8212; you just need to set it up once, and it’ll add a bit of content before and after your posts in your website’s RSS feed, automatically.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This way, even if content scrapers re-publish your content, Google will still recognize you as the original author of your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part? Since you’ll add the links to your posts in the RSS feed, your website content won’t be affected at all.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That means visitors to your website will never see it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you update to All in One SEO 3.7, you&#8217;ll find your RSS Content Settings under <strong>General Settings</strong>, just above Advanced Settings.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/rss-content-settings.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-15156\" width=\"620\" height=\"330\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/rss-content-settings.jpg 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/rss-content-settings-600x319.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/rss-content-settings-300x160.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/rss-content-settings-470x250.jpg 470w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/rss-content-settings-100x53.jpg 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/rss-content-settings-150x80.jpg 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/rss-content-settings-200x106.jpg 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/rss-content-settings-450x240.jpg 450w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Read our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/documentation/rss-content-settings/\">RSS content settings documentation</a> for more details on how to set up your RSS Content Settings for your website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see a list of all the changes and improvements in this update in the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-changelog/\">changelog</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As we develop the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">best SEO plugin for WordPress</a>, we’ll be back for more announcements. So stay tuned for upcoming announcements, because we have plenty more features planned for you.&nbsp;And if you haven’t done so already, click here to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-pro-version/\">get started with All in One SEO today</a>!\n\n</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-all-in-one-seo-3-7-rss-feed/\">Announcing All in One SEO 3.7: Control Your RSS Feed Footer in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-all-in-one-seo-3-7-rss-feed/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"6\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"WordPress XML Sitemaps vs All in One SEO: Which Is Better?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:162:\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-xml-sitemaps-vs-all-in-one-seo-sitemaps/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=wordpress-xml-sitemaps-vs-all-in-one-seo-sitemaps\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-xml-sitemaps-vs-all-in-one-seo-sitemaps/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 04 Aug 2020 16:14:33 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"xml sitemaps\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=14477\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:607:\"<p>Recently it was announced that the upcoming WordPress 5.5 update scheduled for August 11, 2020 will include built-in XML sitemaps without a plugin required. This new XML sitemaps feature will help users who don’t have an SEO plugin like All&#8201;&#8230;&#8201;<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-xml-sitemaps-vs-all-in-one-seo-sitemaps/\" class=\"excerpt-more-link\">Continue reading</a></p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-xml-sitemaps-vs-all-in-one-seo-sitemaps/\">WordPress XML Sitemaps vs All in One SEO: Which Is Better?</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Keri Engel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9914:\"<p>Recently it was announced that the upcoming <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/news/whats-coming-in-wordpress-5-5-features-and-screenshots/\">WordPress 5.5 update</a> scheduled for August 11, 2020 will include built-in XML sitemaps without a plugin required.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This new XML sitemaps feature will help users who don’t have an SEO plugin like All in One SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re already an All in One SEO user, you don’t have to worry. You already have sitemaps plus all the other SEO tools you need to boost your website traffic, and <strong>there’s nothing you need to do</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this guide, we’ll explain what this update means, what’s the difference between WordPress 5.5 XML sitemaps and All in One SEO, and answer your most common questions about this new update.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get started with a simple definition…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What Is an XML Sitemap and Why Do You Need It?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>An XML sitemap is a simple list of all the content on your website. The sitemap makes it easy for search engine bots to crawl and index your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>XML stands for eXtensible Markup Language. It’s a markup language similar to HTML, but its main purpose is to organize data.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your XML sitemap file is hidden from your human visitors, but search engines like Google can see it. The sitemap helps search engine bots to easily see all the content on your site in one place.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Why do you need a sitemap?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Without one, the only way for those bots to find all your content is by following links on your site. So, if you have any pages on your site that aren’t linked to often, or it takes a lot of links to reach a certain page, there’s a chance that Google’s bots won’t find those pages and they’ll never end up in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another reason you’d want a sitemap is so you can tell Google which pages you DON’T want it to list in search results. Removing some pages from search results, like thank you pages or media attachment pages, can help you <strong>get more traffic from Google</strong> because the search engines will only focus on your highest quality content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s why All in One SEO makes it easy to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/documentation/beginners-guide-to-xml-sitemaps/\">create a custom XML sitemap in WordPress and submit it to Google</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s take a quick look at this feature and how it works.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why Use All in One SEO Sitemaps?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>All in One SEO’s XML sitemaps are easy to use, and they also offer all the features you need to optimize your site for maximum traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can automatically generate a custom sitemap and submit it to Google, Bing, Yahoo, Yandex, and other search engines.  All in One SEO will also automatically notify each one whenever you publish, update, or delete content on your site. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With All in One SEO, you can make sure that Google knows which pages are the most important on your site, and only ranks your high-quality content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You get to choose to include or exclude:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>images and galleries</li><li>password-protected posts</li><li>custom post types</li><li>media attachment pages</li><li>archive pages for tags, categories, authors</li><li>and more</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"469\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-sitemap-settings.png\" alt=\"aioseo sitemap settings\" class=\"wp-image-22758\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-sitemap-settings.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-sitemap-settings-300x199.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/aioseo-sitemap-settings-600x399.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Your sitemaps will always be dynamically generated. That means that your sitemap is always up to date whenever it’s visited.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>How does that compare with the new default sitemaps?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>All in One SEO and WordPress 5.5 XML Sitemaps</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In the update scheduled for August 11, 2020, WordPress will include basic XML sitemaps without a plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, the sitemap will include all your posts, post types, categories, tags, and archive pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s no way to customize your sitemaps or remove specific pages without knowing PHP code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, you’d have to customize this code to remove certain sitemaps from your site:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"621\" height=\"363\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/wordpress-xml-sitemap-without-plugin.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-14478\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/wordpress-xml-sitemap-without-plugin.png 621w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/wordpress-xml-sitemap-without-plugin-600x351.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/wordpress-xml-sitemap-without-plugin-300x175.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/wordpress-xml-sitemap-without-plugin-428x250.png 428w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/wordpress-xml-sitemap-without-plugin-100x58.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/wordpress-xml-sitemap-without-plugin-150x88.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/wordpress-xml-sitemap-without-plugin-200x117.png 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/wordpress-xml-sitemap-without-plugin-450x263.png 450w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>The good news is, <strong>if you’re using the latest version of All in One SEO, you don’t need to do anything</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As long as you&#8217;ve updated to the latest version of All in One SEO, the default WordPress sitemaps will be automatically turned off. Your All in One SEO sitemaps will take priority.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not using All in One SEO yet?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want more control over your sitemaps, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-pro-version/\">All in One SEO</a> is the way to go.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to the custom sitemaps feature, you’ll also get access to other features to skyrocket your search traffic like:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>On Page SEO Optimization</strong>: add meta title, description, keywords, and other tags for on-page SEO optimization</li><li><strong>Schema Support</strong>: unlock complete support for Google Knowledge Graph and Schema.org snippets</li><li><strong>Image and Video SEO</strong>: optimize your images and get 1-click support for video sitemap, so you can rank in Google&#8217;s video carousel widget and grow your traffic</li><li><strong>Automatic Search Engine Notification</strong>: automatically notify search engines like Google and Bing about changes to your site</li><li><strong>WooCommerce SEO</strong>: get advanced eCommerce SEO support for WooCommerce, so you can optimize product pages, product categories, and more</li><li><strong>Social Media Integration</strong>: easily control how your content and thumbnails look on Facebook, Twitter, and other social media networks</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>And more…</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-pro-version\">Click here to get started with All in One SEO today!</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Still have questions? Keep reading…&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What does the XML sitemap in WordPress 5.5 do?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress 5.5 will introduce built-in XML sitemaps. The sitemaps will automatically include your homepage, all public posts, categories and tags, and author archives. This includes anything you might have no-indexed, which can cause errors on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress 5.5 XML sitemaps are very basic and don’t include video sitemaps or Google News sitemaps, so your site won’t show up in video carousels or Google News.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s no way to customize the sitemaps without knowing PHP code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Do I still need All in One SEO now that WordPress has its own sitemap?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, All in One SEO integrates seamlessly with WordPress 5.5 and allows you to customize your XML sitemaps so you can boost your traffic and prevent errors in Google Search Console.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It gives you all the features you need to optimize your site for maximum search traffic, including on-page optimizations, SEO titles and meta descriptions, image SEO, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/documentation/video-sitemap/\">video sitemaps</a>, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/documentation/google-news-sitemap/\">Google News sitemaps</a>, local SEO, WooCommerce SEO, and much more. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">Click here to see all the features of All in One SEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Do I need to disable my WordPress XML sitemap?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>No, All in One SEO will automatically disable it for you, to prevent the bots from getting confused or finding the wrong one. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s no need to take any action if you’re already updated. If you&#8217;re using an earlier version than 3.6.2, please make sure to update to the latest version of All in One SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Have more questions? Please <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/contact/\">get in touch</a>, we’re happy to help.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thank you for all your support in making All in One SEO the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">best SEO plugin for WordPress</a>!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not using it yet? What are you waiting for?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-pro-version/\">Click here to get started with All in One SEO today!</a><br></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-xml-sitemaps-vs-all-in-one-seo-sitemaps/\">WordPress XML Sitemaps vs All in One SEO: Which Is Better?</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-xml-sitemaps-vs-all-in-one-seo-sitemaps/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"Introducing Local SEO: Boost Your Google Business Listings\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:106:\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-local-seo/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=introducing-local-seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-local-seo/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 09 Jul 2020 19:27:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"google business listings\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"local seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=13393\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:539:\"<p>It’s only been a short while since we announced the release of our Google News Sitemap feature to help your news content rank faster. But during that time, we’ve been hard at work putting the finishing touches on today’s new&#8201;&#8230;&#8201;<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-local-seo/\" class=\"excerpt-more-link\">Continue reading</a></p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-local-seo/\">Introducing Local SEO: Boost Your Google Business Listings</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Keri Engel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7574:\"<p>It’s only been a short while since we announced the release of our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-google-news-sitemaps/\">Google News Sitemap</a> feature to help your news content rank faster. But during that time, we’ve been hard at work putting the finishing touches on today’s new release.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Today we’re happy to announce the new Local Business SEO addon for <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-pro-version/\">Business and Agency plans</a>, designed to make it much easier to get more search traffic to your local business website!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Help Local People Find Your Business</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Local search has exploded recently with “near me” and “close by” searches growing by over 900% in only 2 years. And when you consider that <strong>97% of people learn more about local companies online</strong> than anywhere else, it makes sense to optimize your website for that traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Google’s local business structured data added to your website, you’re able to provide Google with more information about your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When users search for a business (for example, NYC animal shelter), search results may show a Knowledge Graph card featuring businesses related to their search, putting your company right at the top of the results.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"795\" height=\"421\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/google-business-listings.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13400\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/google-business-listings.png 795w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/google-business-listings-600x318.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/google-business-listings-300x159.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/google-business-listings-768x407.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/google-business-listings-472x250.png 472w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/google-business-listings-100x53.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/google-business-listings-150x79.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/google-business-listings-200x106.png 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/google-business-listings-450x238.png 450w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding structured data to your website isn’t easy if you’re not a developer. You need to insert specific properties to your site’s code in the right way. If you don’t know what you’re doing and add it to the wrong place, it might not work. Even worse, you could mess up your code, breaking your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Easily Enhance Your Local Business Search</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With the Local Business SEO addon to All in One SEO, our goal is to make it as easy as possible to get your business featured in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, all it takes for <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-pro-version/\">Business and Agency plan</a> users to enhance their local SEO easily is to activate the new addon.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"795\" height=\"514\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-seo-addon.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13401\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-seo-addon.png 795w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-seo-addon-600x388.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-seo-addon-300x194.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-seo-addon-768x497.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-seo-addon-387x250.png 387w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-seo-addon-100x65.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-seo-addon-150x97.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-seo-addon-200x129.png 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-seo-addon-450x291.png 450w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then it’s simply a case of entering your business information and saving your changes, no coding required!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can include several different types of information, such as your business type, name, address, phone number, and image. Plus, you can enter your price range and the days and times you’re open.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"795\" height=\"506\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-schema-settings.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13402\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-schema-settings.png 795w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-schema-settings-600x382.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-schema-settings-300x191.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-schema-settings-768x489.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-schema-settings-393x250.png 393w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-schema-settings-100x64.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-schema-settings-150x95.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-schema-settings-200x127.png 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-schema-settings-450x286.png 450w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After, you increase the chances of local searchers finding your business, resulting in <strong>higher click-through rates and conversions</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"795\" height=\"553\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-search.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13403\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-search.png 795w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-search-600x417.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-search-300x209.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-search-768x534.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-search-359x250.png 359w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-search-100x70.png 100w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-search-150x104.png 150w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-search-200x139.png 200w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/local-business-search-450x313.png 450w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>See our documentation for more details on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/documentation/local-business-schema/\">how to set up local business schema with All in One SEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see a list of all the changes and improvements in this update in the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-changelog/\">changelog</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ll be back again soon with more exciting updates as we work to create the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">best SEO plugin for WordPress</a>. So please keep a lookout on our blog for the next announcement.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you haven&#8217;t done so already, click here to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/all-in-one-seo-pack-pro-version/\">get started with All in One SEO today</a>!<br></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-local-seo/\">Introducing Local SEO: Boost Your Google Business Listings</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-local-seo/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"9\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:24:\"https://aioseo.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"\n	hourly	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"\n	1	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:13:{s:6:\"server\";s:12:\"nginx/1.19.0\";s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Mon, 21 Dec 2020 08:29:57 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:10:\"set-cookie\";s:50:\"PHPSESSID=91b89fd88b8c970b7944a98106fcea79; path=/\";s:7:\"expires\";s:29:\"Thu, 19 Nov 1981 08:52:00 GMT\";s:13:\"cache-control\";s:35:\"no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate\";s:6:\"pragma\";s:8:\"no-cache\";s:13:\"last-modified\";s:29:\"Thu, 17 Dec 2020 19:48:47 GMT\";s:4:\"etag\";s:34:\"\"f08a363eecd586b678401e7b6c5f9a86\"\";s:4:\"link\";s:55:\"<https://aioseo.com/wp-json/>; rel=\"https://api.w.org/\"\";s:25:\"strict-transport-security\";s:16:\"max-age=15768000\";s:3:\"via\";s:10:\"1.1 google\";s:7:\"alt-svc\";s:5:\"clear\";}}s:5:\"build\";s:14:\"20200706095936\";}', 'no');
